


translate English day6_my_ce7fd2b8:


    br "\n Maya Elbeth is an angel. {w}And I'll tell you why."


translate English day6_my_a209896c:


    extend "\n First of all, she's always looking down at the ground or up at the sky. Oh, and she hates standing against the wind."


translate English day6_my_8aacbcb0:


    extend "\n She hardly ever speaks up first, but always wants others to notice her. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_my_2e15ef8b:


    extend "\n Her dainty fingertips are often covered in dirt or soot, and yet her fingernails, resembling tiny grains of rice, always smell like flowery soap. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_my_8f6a64fa:


    extend "\n She never makes eye contact with other people for very long, but she always listens without interrupting, {w}no matter the nature of the conversation."


translate English day6_my_49f4e465:



    nvl clear
    br "\n She always has the same worried expression on her face, whether she's happy or sad. {w}And when holding back tears, she always squishes her mouth shut first."


translate English day6_my_76be76c1:


    extend "\n I know all this because I've been watching her this whole time. {w}She has no angel wings, at least none that human eyes can detect."


translate English day6_my_51c7d0e5:


    extend "\n I know that for a fact. {w}How, you might ask? Because I've seen her fly sometimes."


translate English day6_my_7228e30e:


    extend "\n A young girl trying to fly without wings would be a very sad sight indeed. Don't you agree?"


translate English day6_my_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_my_f6061251:


    nar "Maya stared at the flower bed, hugging her knees to her chest."


translate English day6_my_099ed138:


    nar "I can't bring myself to give my usual greeting. {w}It's mainly due to an odd feeling of hyperawareness."


translate English day6_my_2a1ba27a:


    nar "As I awkwardly sit down, she suddenly notices my presence and turns toward me."


translate English day6_my_4c41fad5:


    nar "Our eyes meet and I struggle to calm my racing heart."


translate English day6_my_1cdffa21:


    pl "Morning, Maya."


translate English day6_my_2fe1d178:


    my "Good morning, [na2]."


translate English day6_my_a4524bcf:


    nar "A thin smile comes over her face.{w} Hearing her voice calms my nerves and soothes my apprehension."


translate English day6_my_13102e63:


    pl "What are you up to?"


translate English day6_my_90aaaa5d:


    my "Oh, I was talking to Mr. Bug."


translate English day6_my_9988fb3d:


    pl "Seriously? Ha ha ha! Stop joking around, Maya!"


translate English day6_my_fddac551:


    nar "I laughed as I approached her, assuming she was teasing me. {w}Which is when I noticed the black bug on the freshly bloomed leaf."


translate English day6_my_f0d65186:


    nar "The bug, which looked like a spider mite or leafminer fly, must have jumped over from one of the rose stalks."


translate English day6_my_36fb0449:


    pl "Oof... I guess we have a bug infestation on our hands. {w}Well, it's only natural for at least a couple bugs to appear in a garden like this."


translate English day6_my_94ceb8cf:


    pl "Don't worry about it, Maya. We'll take care of the bug problem after we catch him!"


translate English day6_my_747464fc:


    my "Oh, but...I was planning on leaving him to go about his buggy business..."


translate English day6_my_29b1c743:


    pl "Just leave him?"


translate English day6_my_bbece6c8:


    my "These little guys chose to live here because of how well my flowers are growing..."


translate English day6_my_bce822f0:


    pl "But they're still so small and still budding, so they'll probably die almost immediately if we leave them alone..."


translate English day6_my_723e52a2:


    my "I mean, bugs die right away if you catch them, right?"


translate English day6_my_bc3a1118:


    pl "That's true. Bugs can kill plants, but plants can't do the same the other way around."


translate English day6_my_fcd57d6a:


    my "Yeah? Is that what you really think, [na2]?"


translate English day6_my_a925eee3:


    pl "So you want to keep them alive?"


translate English day6_my_8d2bb1bb:


    my "I'm actually not sure what to do here... so maybe it's best to wait and see? {w}I do know that it's wrong to kill a living creature, right?"


translate English day6_my_c2bf73f6:


    my "I'll be really sad if the buds I worked so hard to grow died, though..."


translate English day6_my_795832e7:


    my "With that said, is it really okay to kill a bug who is just trying to survive?"


translate English day6_my_d67a859e:


    my "I feel trapped, unable to make a decision. {w}With an angel and a devil on either shoulder, I'm at a standstill."


translate English day6_my_11c77246:


    pl "Maya... Are you okay?"


translate English day6_my_3334fc23:


    my "..."


translate English day6_my_0795c478:


    pl "I can tell you're exhausted. {w}You've had a rough couple of days, huh? Why don't we just sit here on the bench for a bit?"


translate English day6_my_7480d2bb:


    my "Okay..."


translate English day6_my_0239d368:


    nar "She got listlessly to her feet. Then, I settled her down on the nearby bench. {w}Maybe it's my imagination, but she looked like she lost weight, the sight of frail body reminding me of my dream from earlier."


translate English day6_my_a2fcbfe2:


    pl "Do you want me to get you some water?"


translate English day6_my_b1e3d454:


    my "That's okay... I just want you to stay here with me."


translate English day6_my_08c78a73:


    pl "Mm..."


translate English day6_my_2c9e3031:


    nar "We both fall silent once again. {w}I'm happy to sit next to her, though it doesn't look like she's about to speak up any time soon."


translate English day6_my_02927512:


    nar "I decide to open my mouth first, knowing that we'll be sitting here in perpetual silence otherwise."


translate English day6_my_deb7080e:


    pl "The reason you can sympathize so strongly is due to how sweet you are, Maya."


translate English day6_my_43613e49:


    my "I just don't know anything... Everything in my head feels all jumbled.{w} And while I watch, things... Things seem to get more complicated."


translate English day6_my_d3d01587:


    pl "Yeah, there are always times like that. When you focus on one thing for too long, you start overthinking it all,"


translate English day6_my_e5fb29f6:


    pl "and before you realize what's happening, you've already forgotten what the problem was to begin with."


translate English day6_my_a893972a:


    pl "It's called Gezuntight-fall or something complicated like that..."


translate English day6_my_7c16d8fd:


    my "Hey, [na2]. Do you remember our conversation from the other day?"


translate English day6_my_7f7e2522:


    pl "Which one?"


translate English day6_my_eb796d0f:


    my "About the angel..."


translate English day6_my_b47bc570:


    nar "My heart immediately sinks into my stomach."


translate English day6_my_8556a36e:


    pl "Yeah... I remember."


translate English day6_my_f25b222f:


    my "That stuff you said? I think you were right, [na2]..."


translate English day6_my_e375c1b0:


    my "When people or animals suddenly die or have some kind of unfortunate accident..."


translate English day6_my_e3e3e5ee:


    my "Their bad luck is nothing more than a product of karma."


translate English day6_my_91fae28d:


    pl "I mean, basically, yeah."


translate English day6_my_55f10a75:


    my "But there's no way I could ever know exactly what crimes I may have committed in a previous life, right? {w}It doesn't make sense..."


translate English day6_my_42d538c7:


    pl "I agree with you. {w}Listen, Maya."


translate English day6_my_34a5539f:


    pl "I'm not sure why I'm telling you this, but at any rate, {w}where I come from, we're told that God has a reason for everything, even if it seems senseless at first."


translate English day6_my_afb8e2cf:


    pl "They'd often go on and on about this thing called \"karma,\" a mythical phenomenon that we have no way of proving truly exists."


translate English day6_my_62e7ff77:


    pl "It's just a fairy tale created by humanity to help explain things that don't make sense. {w}It's not something designed to torment yourself with."


translate English day6_my_e168caf9:


    my "Then why do animal, plants, and people die?"


translate English day6_my_bd15fca6:


    my "People usually blame misfortune on karma, and say that pestis is punishment. {w}And yet sometimes good people die tragic deaths while bad people live on seemingly forever..."


translate English day6_my_40a64476:


    nar "The very thought I'd try to avoid at all costs suddenly slaps me right in the face."


translate English day6_my_66dce5c9:


    pl "That's true. Hm... {w}How do I put this... {w}I don't think I've ever really thought that hard about why people die."


translate English day6_my_26645b8b:


    nar "When the old lady who lived next door I always said hello to died, I remember going to her funeral and being surrounded by her friends who worked alongside her."


translate English day6_my_ee8f0ae0:


    nar "All they talked about was the topic of life and death."


translate English day6_my_f8c0aee2:


    nar "That the way we die and the length of our lifespan are both predetermined by karma from the moment we're born."


translate English day6_my_cf04b559:


    nar "But I never believed a word of it."


translate English day6_my_dfab3969:


    nar "Freedom does not come to those frightened by God's whims, who seems to enjoy doling out punishments over grace. {w}The way I see it, life is simply unfair--plain and simple."


translate English day6_my_e696c972:


    my "...It's pretty scary."


translate English day6_my_1dde9e4c:


    nar "She murmurs quietly while hunched over, hugging her knees to her chest."


translate English day6_my_aae36ec9:


    my "Death is terrifying."


translate English day6_my_c25717ce:


    nar "I raise my hand and put it on her trembling shoulder as if comforting a child. Maya doesn't brush it away."


translate English day6_my_840f85dc:


    nar "Her back is curved as if to protect her weak body. {w}Naturally, there are no wings sticking out of it."


translate English day6_my_a0b88f43:


    pl "Where did this come from?"


translate English day6_my_ca11a232:


    pl "I can't say you won't die, but when it happens, it'll be sometime in the very distant future. It's not something you need to worry about right now."


translate English day6_my_50f734f2:


    my "It's something I've always worried about. {w}Only God knows who will die and when."


translate English day6_my_34b342d4:


    nar "Her voice, drowning in fear, is lost in the fierce, gusting wind. {w}The spot where my hand is on her back feels warm to the touch. {w}Even I'm scared."


translate English day6_my_810becc2:


    nar "But I'm not fearing my own death--I'm fearing Maya's eventual demise."


translate English day6_my_17000d4b:


    nar "Pestis is, for the most part, irrational, but is it not true that death comes first to those who've lost themselves along the way?"


translate English day6_my_46cf200b:


    nar "If Maya gives up on herself, then I'm afraid the person most at risk of getting infected by Pestis is her."


translate English day6_my_45e66b17:


    pl "You don't have to think about that kind of stuff, Maya... {w}Really, there's no need to."


translate English day6_my_3d39add6:


    nar "I squeeze her shoulder, but I can't see her face with her head still bowed."


translate English day6_my_bade5ef0:


    nar "There's definitely something on her mind. I can tell she's lost in thought, though I can't tell what specifically."


translate English day6_my_710460aa:


    nar "I shake my head in an attempt at stopping the spread of my own bad thoughts {w}and to dispel the murky, disturbing image quickly taking shape in my mind."


translate English day6_my_136eeb79:


    pl "You really need to stop thinking like that."


translate English day6_my_8848edc6:


    nar "Considering that I'm constantly exposed to death to the point where it's simply a part of my everyday life, it's a little bizarre I don't think about it at all."


translate English day6_my_85ab703f:


    nar "How can I simply ignore that I, along with everyone I know, is constantly standing on the edge of an invisible cliff?"


translate English day6_my_cea42d6f:


    nar "The simple answer is it's easy enough to ignore when you can't see it."


translate English day6_my_65638176:


    nar "I can trick myself into thinking I'm standing on a flat plain because I know death isn't imminent."


translate English day6_my_5fcba14d:


    nar "That idle delusion is enough to calm me down in the face of my current formidable situation, distracting me from my surroundings."


translate English day6_my_169ea1c3:


    pl "I'll do whatever I can to protect you from the things that scare you, Maya!"


translate English day6_my_9523e574:


    nar "But burying my face in the sand is what led to yesterday's accident. {w}And we continue to deal with the aftermath of that negligence."


translate English day6_my_476ca104:


    nar "Only I can protect Maya. {w}Only I know specifics regarding the angel's death."


translate English day6_my_246c242a:


    nar "Perhaps Pestis does not choose its victims indiscriminately. {w}Maybe it only visits those who have forgotten how to live?"


translate English day6_my_8055f8e4:


    my "You said something similar on our first day here..."


translate English day6_my_2c5230d7:


    pl "What? I did?"


translate English day6_my_7480d2bb_1:


    my "Yeah..."


translate English day6_my_22231e2e:


    nar "I'm started to get fed up with myself. {w}How can she remember things I've said but I can't remember anything from our first day here?"


translate English day6_my_c06b8ac9:


    nar "I meant everything I said in an attempt to cheer her up as she sat there, openly sobbing. That sincerity is long gone now. {w}All things change eventually--even what lies in our hearts, too."


translate English day6_my_6b830c1b:


    nar "With that said, I've never lied to her, not even once. {w}That much is true."


translate English day6_my_00782940:


    nar "Hope, the future, safety... {w}I'd easily promise all of those things to her, though I have no guarantee of following through."


translate English day6_my_75b1a907:


    my "Once you move over to the Magic Department, [na2], I just... I don't know what I'll do without you..."


translate English day6_my_15618a31:


    pl "Where's that coming from? You're acting like you'll never see me again."


translate English day6_my_1200ef98:


    my "That's what you say now, but...we'll see..."


translate English day6_my_bc568897:


    pl "You're joking, right?"


translate English day6_my_14e9a4f8:


    my "Words aren't proof of anything and they certainly can't guarantee a course of action..."


translate English day6_my_b0870d80:


    pl "So does that mean you don't trust me to do what I say?"


translate English day6_my_4ad77234:


    nar "Maya squeezes my hand, wavering in the air uncertainly."


translate English day6_my_bc15385b:


    nar "I can feel a faint trembling through her grip. Not from her hand this time, but from mine."


translate English day6_my_ca268763:


    nar "I hadn't thought about it at all. {w}She's always been by my side, right there whenever I needed her. {w}What will happen when that's not the case?"


translate English day6_my_3744197d:


    nar "What will happen to us?"


translate English day6_my_986761a7:


    pl "Maya... Do you not want me to go?"


translate English day6_my_1eda4d8e:


    my "...What would you do if I said yes, I don't want you to go?"


translate English day6_my_539b421f:


    nar "I shut my mouth, unable to answer. {w}I can't bring myself to make another promise I can't be sure I can keep."


translate English day6_my_4115b97a:


    nar "I'm afraid my clumsily spoken promise will only hurt her again, and that this time, I'll never get her back."


translate English day6_my_35ab8780:


    nar "I think I know understand what she meant when she told me once how she hates seeing another person in pain."


translate English day6_my_d2859aa4:


    nar "Up until now, we've been practically inseparable, spending most of our time together. {w}We were bound together by life itself, so much stronger than the fickleness of fate."


translate English day6_my_d1f025a7:


    nar "Even her grief binds us together."


translate English day6_my_1f433868:


    nar "And the more I feel that grief emanating from her and the more she suffers, {w}the more pain I feel knowing that I should be protecting her."


translate English day6_my_e9af0fb1:


    nar "All we can do is pray. {w}It's the only option we have when faced with another human's grief."


translate English day6_my_bff71bc6:


    pl "Have I really helped you that much, Maya?"


translate English day6_my_4c9c5b04:


    my "Yes, you have, in so many ways..."


translate English day6_my_f0d42bc0:


    pl "Not like that. What I mean is..."


translate English day6_my_affd4591:


    my "I don't want you to have to feel responsible for any of this, [na2]."


translate English day6_my_ca4d0e01:


    pl "That's not it. I want to be someone in your life you can rely on."


translate English day6_my_a9998edf:


    my "...Don't go out of your way for me."


translate English day6_my_27eae68c:


    nar "But I'm not like everyone else."


translate English day6_my_3cc3ea54:


    nar "At the very least, I refuse to watch her pain from a comfortable distance while praying to some unknown God."


translate English day6_my_81402562:


    nar "I want to do it. I want to be the one to make her happy. Not God--me."


translate English day6_my_7a0ddd04:


    nar "I'm sorry if I accidentally got her hopes up in the past only to let her down. But this time, I mean every single word."


translate English day6_my_b1d20fea:


    nar "And I hope that more than anything, she sees that."


translate English day6_my_7084d7af:


    pl "That's right. I want to make you happy. {w}I love you, Maya."


translate English day6_my_785293e7:


    nar "Love. {w}That unfamiliar word weighs far heavier in my heart, feeling so different from its vague existence within my jumbled thoughts."


translate English day6_my_6ec73a2c:


    nar "What I'm feeling right now is love. I am sure, without a doubt, that there's nothing else this feeling could possibly be."


translate English day6_my_8790043f:


    nar "I've never felt this way about anyone before. {w}And I'm not about to let this chance slip through my fingers."


translate English day6_my_4155f64e:


    nar "I won't lie to her. I want to be there for her, right by her side."


translate English day6_my_893178b1:


    nar "I want to make her happy. {w}I want nothing more in life right now than to be with her, forever and ever."


translate English day6_my_a4dd5355:


    nar "I wish I never had to let go of her hand, which she gave to me first."


translate English day6_my_5b409c35:


    nar "Right now, I feel like I can do just about anything."


translate English day6_my_3334fc23_1:


    my "..."


translate English day6_my_c9969f3f:


    nar "The noon time bell rings out, and she lets go of my hand. {w}It slipped from my grasp so absurdly easy despite my tight grip."


translate English day6_my_aa30516a:


    nar "We exchange vague glances without actually meeting each other's gaze. {w}I'm self-conscious about the cold sweat in the palm of my hand."


translate English day6_my_0907a6ea:


    my "I'm hungry..."


translate English day6_my_c81e0703:


    nar "She gives me a slight smile when she finally looks me in the eyes."


translate English day6_my_6a76be26:


    pl "Let's go get something to eat then?"


translate English day6_my_7480d2bb_2:


    my "Okay..."


translate English day6_cr_1939eda4:



    nvl clear
    br "\n One day, I received a letter from her.{w} It was written on dark brown letter stationery with cute sealing wax.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_cr_5e7ae49c:


    extend "\n Her letters were neatly written--and there were a lot of them.{w} It was very wordy, but its contents were rather silly in many places. It made me laugh several times.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_cr_c2b6e6d8:


    extend "\n But as my hands flipped through the papers, they trembled.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_cr_e4094dbb:


    extend "\n Because I already know that somewhere in the final section, or perhaps somewhere in between, this letter would contain things I have no idea about.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_cr_6735b502:


    extend "\n She wrote as neatly as an adult would, but the rounded letters naturally cause her voice to come to mind."


translate English day6_cr_4cd882ce:


    extend "\n And that's why I get even more scared.{w} Because there's only one thing she--a lover of conversation--wouldn't be able to express in writing."


translate English day6_cr_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_cr_e66e7fd6:


    nar "Ugh. My hands started shaking again.{w} This ticklish feeling in my palms is always awful."


translate English day6_cr_fc0a7b91:


    nar "The emergency stairs are always quiet, but they're even more silent right now, probably because I left my room earlier than usual."


translate English day6_cr_5cf64a88:


    nar "They're also damp in here because of the rain--it starts and stops on a whim, as if to make fun of humans."


translate English day6_cr_26f3a0a2:


    nar "Right now, I'm sitting alone in this dismal place."


translate English day6_cr_510b8045:


    nar "I've been thinking about Claire ever since she had to hurry home."


translate English day6_cr_b03a3f8b:


    nar "Now that I knew her secret, try as I might to keep a level head, I just can't do it."


translate English day6_cr_a28bd80f:


    nar "Ms. Grette's dry note about her family situation-- about that trembling voice, about those frightened eyes."


translate English day6_cr_6dfb01ba:


    nar "I don't want to remember them, but they come to mind anyway. It's agonizing."


translate English day6_cr_ae1ef09b:


    nar "That's why I'm here.{w} Even though I know there's no guarantee she'll come here.{w} Even I think it was a silly idea."


translate English day6_cr_81d1de7e:


    nar "I could still go back to the dorm, waste some time there, and then come again.{w} That's the idea looping through my head."


translate English day6_cr_9125610c:


    nar "But I just can't seem to get back up."


translate English day6_cr_dd315f5e:


    nar "I've been worried.{w} I thought I'd be able to see her again, have a few laughs--but that belief is unfounded, and I'm not confident in it."


translate English day6_cr_38a6a565:


    nar "But I just want to make sure she's okay as soon as possible."


translate English day6_cr_c6561303:


    pl "*cough*..."


translate English day6_cr_d984dea9:


    nar "I knew we should have planned to meet somewhere else.{w} Not exactly the cleanest air for a prim and proper girl like her."


translate English day6_cr_5cb5453a:


    nar "If she arrives, maybe I'll bring her to the terrace outside."


translate English day6_cr_59bacd7d:


    nar "Both of us would definitely prefer a refreshing walk outside to shutting ourselves up in this suffocating room."


translate English day6_cr_ebb51360:


    nar "Maya will probably be there too.{w} We could all hang out together, just like the first day we met."


translate English day6_cr_173fd790:


    nar "Maya kept pretty quiet back then, so maybe the two of us could tell Claire about the events of the past few days."


translate English day6_cr_d91952a5:


    nar "I bet Claire's eyes will light up when she hears it--she loves temple incidents and stories."


translate English day6_cr_3196694c:


    nar "Why couldn't I talk to her about that?{w} Well, yesterday, I couldn't exactly get my words in order."


translate English day6_cr_cf90e95e:


    nar "I'd brought some surprising gossip for her, only for that bombshell to come out first thing.{w} But just you wait--today will be different."


translate English day6_cr_eb1e660c:


    pl "......"


translate English day6_cr_227f8636:


    nar "Feeling like my blood isn't pumping, I push my thumb hard against my palm.{w} The quiet darkness around me makes me feel so sleepy."


translate English day6_cr_b24b93cf:


    nar "Maybe she's not coming today."


translate English day6_cr_621d9f38:


    nar "She said she had something urgent to talk with her parents about, right?{w} I really don't understand why I can't leave such a small girl alone."


translate English day6_cr_3a019618:


    nar "I rest my head on my knees and run a hand through my hair--there's sweat on my brow.{w} Now that I think of it, I feel like I closed the window because I didn't know when the rain would start again."


translate English day6_cr_6a3045c6:


    nar "Eventually, the suffocating feeling pushed me up and out of my seat."


translate English day6_cr_5a98a6b9:


    cr "Please wait!" with sshake


translate English day6_cr_e9167ba8:


    nar "A flustered voice rings out from beside me.{w} I rush back down the stairs I was about to ascend."


translate English day6_cr_191d1af6:


    nar "A pure-white girl leaps into view and runs towards me.{w} Unusually, the sound of high heels echoes."


translate English day6_cr_69548934:


    cr "Good morning, Lord [na]!"


translate English day6_cr_2ca126a3:


    nar "In contrast to Claire's peppy greeting, I'm still dumbfounded.{w} My heart is pounding.{w} Was it because I waited so long? Or because she appeared so suddenly?"


translate English day6_cr_c70f6b56:


    pl "Claire, uh...{w} What's with the getup?"


translate English day6_cr_713b4e33:


    cr "Oh... This? I actually had some wedding pictures taken today."


translate English day6_cr_7c4c73ac:


    cr "This is one of the dresses I used for the photoshoot.{w} How does it look?"


translate English day6_cr_12d870b1:


    pl "How does it look? What kind of crazy person would wear clothes like THAT to the temple?"


translate English day6_cr_d5d4c785:


    cr "I really wanted to show them to you.{w} I came as soon as the pictures were done!{w} You should be thanking me."


translate English day6_cr_4f0bab6c:


    cr "Because you're never getting another chance to see this again! *twirl*"


translate English day6_cr_f3d739e9:


    nar "She's sure in a good mood, despite how I feel..."


translate English day6_cr_195c15a1:


    pl "Wedding pictures?{w} You're getting married, huh?{w} After all."


translate English day6_cr_192d4a69:


    cr "Yes, in one month.{w} After all, as you said."


translate English day6_cr_2edf4120:


    nar "As soon as I saw her clothes, my displeasure came into focus.{w} I guess our talk yesterday meant nothing."


translate English day6_cr_7db44605:


    cr "I'll just take a seat right here."


translate English day6_cr_7f17d7b7:


    pl "A seat with that expensive dress on?"


translate English day6_cr_e2feea75:


    cr "I wouldn't have come in the dress if I wasn't prepared to get it dirty!"


translate English day6_cr_5df96171:


    nar "Stubbornly, she sits down next to me.{w} Everything feels so out of place now, with that gorgeous dress of hers juxtaposed with this crude, dreary place."


translate English day6_cr_55579813:


    nar "She's been holding onto the hem, so it's probably fine, but one of the long lace ribbons is dragging on the ground."


translate English day6_cr_59840b90:


    nar "It's not just her clothing; her attitude stands out too.{w} She's like someone who only resembles the girl I met before--or someone I don't know at all."


translate English day6_cr_3669c2dd:


    cr "In any case, I didn't think you would have been here so early."


translate English day6_cr_11a2fa53:


    cr "I shouldn't have hurried.{w} It's very hard to run in heels, you know."


translate English day6_cr_22d5f442:


    pl "I really didn't think you'd be here this early either."


translate English day6_cr_5291c554:


    pl "And what was with that shout before?{w} What would you have done if it hadn't been me on the stairs?"


translate English day6_cr_89fe44df:


    cr "You say that, but you flew down those stairs as well, Lord [na].{w} What would YOU have done if you'd been hearing things?"


translate English day6_cr_294d6345:


    pl "I'm not so tired I'd be hearing your voice out of thin air..."


translate English day6_cr_3ff4d864:


    nar "With a relaxed sort of face, Claire removes her white shoes and places them under the handrail.{w} The side of her little finger is red and peeling."


translate English day6_cr_583e80f6:


    cr "Pfft! You just can't take your eyes off me. You're such a lech!!!"


translate English day6_cr_d95a4a0b:


    pl "Oh, barefeet? Looks like you're the unrefined one today, little miss Claire!"


translate English day6_cr_ffe7baa7:


    cr "It's only for a few minutes.{w} Also, in summer, you're supposed to put shoes on bare feet."


translate English day6_cr_06b9686c:


    cr "At the temple, the rules say to always wear stockings when wearing shoes, so I don't blame you for not knowing."


translate English day6_cr_9b208d06:


    pl "That's news to me..."


translate English day6_cr_dcc35b38:


    cr "Oh? You weren't aware?{w} Even the men at the temple generally need to wear black tights and heeled boots."


translate English day6_cr_2d0f2b33:


    cr "They look quite good on Maya, but you really are the picture of a delinquent with those clothes."


translate English day6_cr_91c4f2fb:


    pl "It's no big deal. The disposal team lets you wear whatever anyway."


translate English day6_cr_426e5569:


    cr "Oh? This time, that's news to me!{w} I wonder just what bishop decided on that rule?"


translate English day6_cr_1319fc46:


    pl "Actually, it was Bishop [na].{w} He just made it a rule."


translate English day6_cr_46918d98:


    pl "Also, I don't think someone who comes to the temple in a wedding dress has much place to talk about other people's clothing."


translate English day6_cr_2b9c8e85:


    cr "Hey! I came all this way to show it to you!"


translate English day6_cr_a3695029:


    pl "I never asked you to wear something like that.{w} I didn't even want to see it anyway."


translate English day6_cr_86fbfb32:


    nar "My voice sinks in spite of me.{w} Claire, reading the mood, keeps her mouth shut and strokes one of my fingers with her hand."


translate English day6_cr_0dc4fa37:


    nar "There's no light in here, but one gap between her little fingers sometimes sparkles.{w} Did she receive that ring last night?{w} Or was it just for the pictures?"


translate English day6_cr_a621e141:


    cr "...I did a lot of thinking after going home yesterday, you know."


translate English day6_cr_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "......"


translate English day6_cr_0c7ec215:


    cr "But there's simply nothing to be done.{w} Complaints will get me nowhere.{w} My parents have raised me from birth."


translate English day6_cr_2b059cb5:


    cr "I've always gone along with their decisions.{w} I've come much too far to change that in the span of a single night."


translate English day6_cr_83c51c6f:


    pl "But this isn't right."


translate English day6_cr_ec72cdb3:


    cr "What isn't right is you continuing to deny it, even now."


translate English day6_cr_cd125316:


    pl "But you said so yesterday, too!"


translate English day6_cr_862622b0:


    cr "Because this isn't one of those wait-and-it-goes-away problems.{w} Or were you planning on solving it yourself?"


translate English day6_cr_56ddec00:


    pl "I...!"


translate English day6_cr_a811b472:


    nar "I can't respond.{w} I could never solve it--I've known that from the start."


translate English day6_cr_d9b06467:


    nar "As I look at her wedding dress and we talk about marriage, I can't help but think of Arnie."


translate English day6_cr_d20ab3dd:


    nar "Claire may be younger than me, but thinking about another woman in front of her?{w} I'm the absolute worst."


translate English day6_cr_16993367:


    cr "Words have a lot of weight to them, don't they?"


translate English day6_cr_b3bc6e79:


    nar "It's frankly a shock--and laughable--that the most loose-lipped of all the people I know would say something like that."


translate English day6_cr_6e6589b5:


    nar "But her remark doesn't seem like it's just to scold me.{w} It's a complicated feeling, like introspection or sorrow--and it feels like she wants me to answer."


translate English day6_cr_59929964:


    nar "Just like how I felt before."


translate English day6_cr_222d99e5:


    pl "Your hair's a mess, you know."


translate English day6_cr_72c7b62b:


    cr "Pardon me?!{w} That certainly isn't something to say to a lady in public!"


translate English day6_cr_d3cd8a86:


    pl "I said it because you'd probably be embarrassed leaving it like that!"


translate English day6_cr_84c5ba61:


    cr "It's because of the hair ornaments holding it together.{w} If I pull on it, my hair will come out of its style, too."


translate English day6_cr_9c31448c:


    pl "I don't know. Looks pretty simple to me..."


translate English day6_cr_0aeb784a:


    cr "Would you like to give it a try, then?"


translate English day6_cr_4722184f:


    pl "I actually happen to be an expert at these things, I'll have you know.{w} You can leave this to me."


translate English day6_cr_52eac0fa:


    nar "She shoves her fine hair into my palms.{w} The closer I get to her little head, the more a warm dampness I can feel."


translate English day6_cr_b58be531:


    nar "It's hot in this stairwell since there's no ventilation.{w} Each time I unravel one of her clumps of fine hair, my fingers get a little bit damper."


translate English day6_cr_9d32ad2c:


    nar "Suddenly I feel mischievous, so I audibly blow onto her.{w} Her shoulders, which I can see through the translucent lace, shake with a small shiver."


translate English day6_cr_9f30022e:


    cr "Hee hee hee. It is summer, isn't it?"


translate English day6_cr_c1f70b7d:


    pl "Cooler now?"


translate English day6_cr_af936146:


    cr "Yes.{w} And how does my hair feel to you?{w} I put a lot into maintaining it, you know!"


translate English day6_cr_94107e14:


    pl "It's really, really fine.{w} Like if I pulled on it a tiny bit, it would come right out."


translate English day6_cr_2a0ad1fa:


    cr "Oh, but it's surprisingly sturdy.{w} A pull wouldn't be enough to rip much out."


translate English day6_cr_f9c1dbaf:


    nar "Is she speaking from experience...?"


translate English day6_cr_6f7f7fe1:


    nar "It's a casual question, but I stop myself from saying it, since it would ruin the mood we'd finally softened."


translate English day6_cr_30ebd82f:


    nar "My fingers almost stop as well, but I keep them moving."


translate English day6_cr_c92974d2:


    nar "Her hair isn't just fine, it's long too.{w} To completely undo it, you need to carefully grasp the kinked hairs and smooth them out."


translate English day6_cr_93d5a914:


    nar "Her hair glistens each time I smooth it out, like silken threads used for expensive clothing."


translate English day6_cr_702dff1a:


    pl "Seems like it's unusual to see azure hair like yours in the capital."


translate English day6_cr_c4c6ae9b:


    cr "Azure hair?{w} I've only ever been told that it's a light blue color."


translate English day6_cr_06d7dd24:


    pl "It's not exactly light blue.{w} Haven't you ever heard of the color azure?"


translate English day6_cr_dc0d537c:


    cr "I have, but it doesn't make much sense to me.{w} You mean the color of the sky, yes?"


translate English day6_cr_867710e5:


    pl "I guess it doesn't make sense because the sky here in the capital is always hazy or pitch black."


translate English day6_cr_e92521e2:


    cr "Then the sky is this color in your homeland, Lord [na]?"


translate English day6_cr_d6b0c8c1:


    pl "Something like it.{w} The air's so dirty here...{w} I almost can't believe it's on the same continent."


translate English day6_cr_084adb20:


    cr "Well, this is fairly normal for us.{w} But I'd like to see what color the sky really is at some point in my life!"


translate English day6_cr_a2db2446:


    cr "It's starting to seem ever so romantic to me."


translate English day6_cr_5c6549fd:


    cr "Perhaps it's like the sea?{w} They say that long ago, it was a true blue color, as though a painter created it..."


translate English day6_cr_21f8f6bf:


    pl "Yeah, I've heard that too."


translate English day6_cr_8e787894:


    pl "We don't have a sea in my homeland, so I don't really know what the real thing is like...{w} Is it different from rivers?"


translate English day6_cr_546151b8:


    cr "You truly don't know anything, do you, Lord [na]?{w} A sea is very large and vast."


translate English day6_cr_f526edf6:


    cr "And in a way, this very continent floats on top of a sea."


translate English day6_cr_03cbb33a:


    pl "Meaning if you had a boat, you could go just about anywhere, huh?"


translate English day6_cr_1d203afd:


    cr "Ideally, yes.{w} Have I sparked your desire for adventure?"


translate English day6_cr_9847da5b:


    pl "Hey, don't just ask me everything! What about you?{w} Don't you like taking trips to foreign places?"


translate English day6_cr_18b6df67:


    cr "Oh, but of course!{w} In fact, I would sneak into my father's luggage just to get a chance to float right in the middle of the continent's sea."


translate English day6_cr_e89d760b:


    cr "But... I have something tying me down here, after all."


translate English day6_cr_63d17e5f:


    pl "Can't you just say it normally?"


translate English day6_cr_dbf6ac06:


    cr "Well, you have your work to do, don't you, Lord [na]?{w} It's much the same as that."


translate English day6_cr_577e6bd0:


    pl "I dunno.{w} If I got the chance, I'd probably toss all the work I'm doing now to the side and go out to enjoy myself."


translate English day6_cr_1cb89a12:


    pl "Just to vent everything in my head, you know?{w} Even if it's only for a couple days."


translate English day6_cr_ccecfeed:


    cr "It sounds like you have a lot of worries."


translate English day6_cr_ba0082fa:


    pl "Not a lot, really... Well, just a little.{w} They're light enough that the wind would carry them away."


translate English day6_cr_b5d2efe7:


    cr "Is that so?{w} Perhaps the same goes for me as well--at least, a little bit."


translate English day6_cr_4abfe7e1:


    nar "I've been taking a lot of care undoing her hair, but two strands of it get stuck to my fingertips."


translate English day6_cr_c45e2a6f:


    nar "Despite how twisted they are, they're so soft.{w} I almost can't even feel them in my hands."


translate English day6_cr_ae74d6bb:


    nar "But as I brush them aside to make sure I got them undone, I find something hidden."


translate English day6_cr_207812b9:


    nar "It's a bruise.{w} On the corner of her temple is a distinct bruise the color of a rotten egg."


translate English day6_cr_68131b7a:


    nar "I feel my heart almost stop.{w} I feel a sudden pressure all through my body, and it causes my movements to stop."


translate English day6_cr_88b46dec:


    nar "My fingertips run out of energy.{w} In front of me now is her hair, glistening with a light sheen, neatly combed like it always is."


translate English day6_cr_dcc58bd1:


    cr "...Lord [na]?"


translate English day6_cr_6d50a25b:


    pl "Huh?"


translate English day6_cr_6879320a:


    cr "It feels quite nice to have someone fix up my hair like this."


translate English day6_cr_e1705cd0:


    pl "I'm sure a proper young lady like you has maids to do it every day."


translate English day6_cr_fbf0a64d:


    cr "Well... It's not exactly the same.{w} And I'm the type who prefers to maintain her own hair."


translate English day6_cr_b53b21e6:


    pl "Are you saying you like it when others fuss over you?"


translate English day6_cr_a73758bc:


    cr "What I mean is, I quite enjoy entrusting my body to someone else without a care in the world."


translate English day6_cr_f819d09c:


    nar "She had to know that wound was there if she'd ever looked in a mirror."


translate English day6_cr_034fc502:


    nar "All of this is a performance--she's showing me the truth."


translate English day6_cr_8121792c:


    nar "The wedding dress she'd kept on, the wound on her head she purposely didn't hide, her meaningful words--everything."


translate English day6_cr_23695e78:


    nar "Yesterday's conversation hasn't been meaningless--in fact, it was the exact opposite.{w} The words I said to her had sprouted into some kind of meaning for her."


translate English day6_cr_3d8783af:


    nar "And now she's trying to show me that.{w} All those ideas aside, I want to comfort her."


translate English day6_cr_dd101fcc:


    nar "I want to put my arms around her, like in a regular movie or a novel.{w} I feel like that's what I'm supposed to do."


translate English day6_cr_44d9a9f7:


    nar "In fact, I feel like that's what she wants most from me right now, and that if I could do it, it would have meaning for me as well.{w} But in the end, I put my hands down."


translate English day6_cr_69f100a7:


    nar "That's something I can't allow myself to do."


translate English day6_cr_e95f9778:


    pl "All done."


translate English day6_cr_56b43a38:


    cr "Thank you!{w} You really are good at this, aren't you?"


translate English day6_cr_11740a29:


    pl "I told you so.{w} I wouldn't brag about stuff I don't think I could handle."


translate English day6_cr_ecbcfa8a:


    cr "I have a question for you, Lord [na].{w} If you were to go on a trip, where would you want to go?"


translate English day6_cr_4461c722:


    pl "I dunno. Just walking around the capital seems fun enough...{w} Actually, I like the mountains better than the sea anyway."


translate English day6_cr_6bb7cdac:


    cr "What? But then what was our conversation for?{w} You've never even been to the sea!"


translate English day6_cr_96bd24ce:


    pl "It's just, I came all the way to the capital, but I haven't had any chance to see it.{w} You remember that movie we talked about before?{w} I was so excited about it, but even now it's slipping away from my memories."


translate English day6_cr_cacb797b:


    cr "Then go see it!{w} You should do everything you want to.{w} I bet you want to try wearing something other than that habit, don't you?"


translate English day6_cr_f6d59fe2:


    pl "Well, sure, but I'd wanna change my hair, too.{w} I heard there are places in the capital that can straighten this crazy hair of mine."


translate English day6_cr_9787e328:


    cr "I very much doubt straight hair would look good on you..."


translate English day6_cr_40c34d0e:


    pl "Stylish means always challenging yourself!"


translate English day6_cr_73d328da:


    cr "I think stylish means always giving reasonable opinions to those close to you.{w} And I like you with a bit of unruly hair."


translate English day6_cr_48113df9:


    pl "Why do you get to decide on my hairstyle?{w} Anyway, you should pick your own place you'd want to go."


translate English day6_cr_4a53c054:


    cr "I wouldn't mind going wherever.{w} I'm sure I'd have fun if I was with you, Lord [na]."


translate English day6_cr_c6bb6d31:


    cr "Oh, I talked about my future plans with my parents yesterday.{w} We decided I wouldn't be having a honeymoon."


translate English day6_cr_396775a6:


    cr "Not that I was hoping for one, but I'm still a little frustrated I won't be going on a trip."


translate English day6_cr_aba93bc6:


    pl "...That's too bad.{w} Or, wait, no, that's a good thing."


translate English day6_cr_ef97d7f1:


    pl "Yeah... We should go on a trip somewhere together.{w} Bet it would be twice as fun if we brought Maya, too."


translate English day6_cr_0b2ff1b6:


    pl "And if you have any friends, call them up too!{w} The more the merrier when it comes to vacations, right?"


translate English day6_cr_917b19b7:


    cr "Come, now. I think that's a stretch, even for you."


translate English day6_cr_95d3345c:


    pl "Well, I have no idea what you mean."


translate English day6_cr_03016cf8:


    nar "Now that I know her situation, I want to be at her side to help her whenever she needs."


translate English day6_cr_8c630135:


    nar "But she seems to want more than that from me.{w} And my heart isn't ready to bear that kind of responsibility."


translate English day6_cr_bcbf9206:


    nar "Without that readiness, I don't have any right to comfort her."


translate English day6_cr_fd828079:


    nar "She still doesn't seem to have confidence in her own feelings, either."


translate English day6_cr_cfd04be9:


    nar "I'm sure that if I tell her more, she'll rethink it.{w} That's what she really wants--from someone she only met by coincidence."


translate English day6_cr_3304f151:


    cr "Come on, say something.{w} I don't mind what. It's just been a little too quiet for me."


translate English day6_cr_71f37f96:


    pl "It's always quiet here.{w} And isn't talking kind of your thing?"


translate English day6_cr_49d715d3:


    cr "I simply can't believe you'd bring a proper young lady like me into a place like this!"


translate English day6_cr_13a708af:


    pl "Ha! I was thinking the same thing before."


translate English day6_cr_2fed06a2:


    cr "While you were waiting for me?"


translate English day6_cr_6fafed35:


    pl "Yeah. Doesn't matter if you're a proper young lady or what--it's a little hard to have a long, cheerful conversation in here."


translate English day6_cr_033b1f0b:


    cr "So you admit you WERE waiting for me!"


translate English day6_cr_8ca15270:


    pl "I wasn't trying to hide it!"


translate English day6_cr_da32f209:


    cr "When we're like this, it makes me feel like everything's at peace...{w} I wonder what normal people think about as they go through their lives."


translate English day6_cr_55cce7e4:


    pl "Nothing.{w} There's no need to cloud your head like that."


translate English day6_cr_609be3db:


    cr "Perhaps that's only what you think.{w} Or are you speaking from experience as a normal person?"


translate English day6_cr_08894969:


    pl "Both.{w} It's a little embarrassing, but until I left the village, I always thought I wasn't normal."


translate English day6_cr_92bea5f0:


    pl "Especially since I wanted to get out of there and go to the capital.{w} But when I really think about it, I was maybe pretty normal after all."


translate English day6_cr_c2b5929d:


    pl "I didn't think about anything else--and that right there's your proof.{w} Back then, that was the biggest problem I thought I'd ever face in my life."


translate English day6_cr_d92c68e5:


    cr "And that's normal?{w} I'd think that's just someone suffering from the current state of things."


translate English day6_cr_151fb0eb:


    pl "Well, sure.{w} I mean, we only call people \"normal\" when we see them having fun lives. Otherwise, we'd just spend all our time frustrated."


translate English day6_cr_048277c6:


    cr "Hmm... I'd like to argue with that, but I don't feel as though you're entirely wrong."


translate English day6_cr_6f801110:


    cr "Perhaps I, too, am not quite normal anymore for thinking about all this."


translate English day6_cr_2abff46b:


    cr "Before, I didn't have many worries or doubts.{w} I wish I could have just stayed focus on protecting my position.{w} But everything's been a mess since yesterday..."


translate English day6_cr_8c848fb1:


    cr "I really have no idea what I'm supposed to do anymore."


translate English day6_cr_968e0899:


    pl "I'm telling you, it was weirder that you didn't think anything of it before."


translate English day6_cr_41bb0cac:


    cr "I was fine being weird, then. It was easier that way.{w} I'm sure you could say the same of yourself, Lord [na]."


translate English day6_cr_f1986699:


    pl "Yeah, I guess you're right.{w} But you were going to have to learn about it one day, you know?"


translate English day6_cr_caeb3d2f:


    pl "But it's not about just you.{w} It's something everyone around you needed to know too."


translate English day6_cr_5a9c8538:


    cr "And now I've realized my situation isn't normal.{w} And it's a little scary..."


translate English day6_cr_5c1d1237:


    pl "It's not your fault.{w} No need for you to be scared."


translate English day6_cr_f2b79cda:


    cr "...I'm sure others would think differently."


translate English day6_cr_227986be:


    cr "I now know that not everyone near me is a good person like you, Lord [na]."


translate English day6_cr_bb7564a9:


    pl "I'm not exactly a good person, you know...{w} I'm just normal."


translate English day6_cr_bc13cf60:


    cr "I suppose, then, that I have many strange people around me."


translate English day6_cr_f9b069a3:


    nar "This is so complicated my head feels like it's splitting in half.{w} I just want Claire to be happy.{w} That's the only thing on my mind right now."


translate English day6_cr_d3e05a15:


    nar "I'm not exactly thinking that I want to do something specific for her, or that she has a problem only I can solve."


translate English day6_cr_efe3c818:


    nar "I've been trying so hard to stop thinking that way."


translate English day6_cr_932500cc:


    nar "I don't have any way to help her.{w} No matter what I'll do, it'll come back to bite her.{w} But she's going back there again.{w} And I want to stop her at any cost."


translate English day6_cr_00ed16f4:


    nar "As I hang my head, I see Claire's skirt hem.{w} Her immaculate white dress is now a murky gray, stained all over with dust."


translate English day6_cr_f4d8eefa:


    pl "...Why DID you wear that here, anyway?{w} Getting it dirty means they'll be angry with you!"


translate English day6_cr_9ce529ab:


    cr "I've already answered that.{w} It was because I wanted to show you, Lord [na]."


translate English day6_cr_d8181fdf:


    pl "But why?"


translate English day6_cr_1a119745:


    cr "Because I thought if I did that... that you would save me, Lord [na]."


translate English day6_cr_87a9190e:


    nar "I look up--our eyes meet.{w} This time, I have a good feeling I won't be able to stop her from saying whatever she's about to say."


translate English day6_cr_294afa42:


    cr "At first, I thought I'd gone crazy."


translate English day6_cr_15400f26:


    cr "But then you told me yesterday to go with whoever my heart chooses."


translate English day6_cr_a8c4d431:


    cr "Experience is important for everything in life, isn't it?{w} So I think that maybe going crazy once in my life isn't so bad."


translate English day6_cr_5cbcb1e4:


    cr "Oh, but don't misunderstand me.{w} I most certainly have not fallen in love with you at first sight."


translate English day6_cr_6b186101:


    cr "You are not my type at all, Lord [na].{w} In fact, you're just the opposite."


translate English day6_cr_f2e54ece:


    cr "I'd heard the rumors, but I was so disappointed when you turned out to be even more... you than they implied.{w} You were a very rude person in general!"


translate English day6_cr_5365faac:


    cr "And I thought that any woman who fell for a man like you would be the most miserable woman in the world."


translate English day6_cr_972518bc:


    cr "But please, don't be offended and think I've only bad things to say about you.{w} That miserable woman turned out to be me, after all."


translate English day6_cr_4f2f7401:


    pl "...What?"


translate English day6_cr_12bb4e79:


    cr "Was I going too fast?{w} I'm sorry. This is the first time I've ever done something like this, and I find myself a little nervous."


translate English day6_cr_d6b49b7b:


    cr "I'm about to be rude, and it's okay if you don't want to tolerate it.{w} So please, Lord [na], save me!"


translate English day6_cr_e0095cff:


    cr "I love you.{w} And this time, I won't run away."


translate English day6_cr_d5ef19ea:


    nar "Maybe I've never really, truly faced Claire before now."


translate English day6_cr_36586369:


    nar "I've always had an easy time talking to her, had fun trading thoughts with her.{w} I knew what she was thinking even if she didn't say it."


translate English day6_cr_032359e3:


    nar "But those were my feelings and mine alone.{w} I hoped they wouldn't come to fruition.{w} I'm sure Claire knew that, too, which was why she never said anything until now."


translate English day6_cr_3faefdcb:


    nar "But even she has her limit.{w} Which means our relationship is also at its limit now.{w} All because I enlightened her."


translate English day6_cr_265f2416:


    nar "She had the wedding dress on, so my mind rushed ahead, thinking she'd already gotten a wedding ring."


translate English day6_cr_e353fb61:


    nar "If I let her get away now, she'll go back there again.{w} To that house. To that man."


translate English day6_cr_eddbf483:


    nar "But all I can do is hesitate."


translate English day6_cr_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "......"


translate English day6_cr_244b56f1:


    cr "Heh... Your face just got so serious."


translate English day6_cr_43489136:


    nar "Perhaps unable to endure the silence, Claire gets up and laughs awkwardly at me."


translate English day6_cr_8714b49f:


    nar "It sounds absurd, but in this moment, I can feel that we each know what the other is thinking."


translate English day6_cr_9df8340b:


    cr "I'm well aware that what I'm asking for is unrealistic."


translate English day6_cr_59872af3:


    cr "I didn't say that because I necessarily expected a favorable response.{w} But I wanted to tell you what I'm feeling."


translate English day6_cr_eb1e660c_3:


    pl "......"


translate English day6_cr_544aee05:


    cr "So thank you so very much for hearing me out. I truly mean it."


translate English day6_cr_c705d525:


    cr "To be honest, I'm happy just for being able to express my opinion to you."


translate English day6_cr_330323f7:


    pl "Claire..."


translate English day6_cr_44f6f8df:


    cr "And I felt that way because I quite enjoy being with you, Lord [na]."


translate English day6_cr_bf848b5c:


    cr "That's how fun it has been for me...{w} So I don't want to make things awkward."


translate English day6_cr_cca07095:


    pl "Then look at me while you talk."


translate English day6_cr_15c476f4:


    cr "......"


translate English day6_cr_d190b3b1:


    nar "With nervousness in my heart, I look at Claire.{w} Her expression is back to normal.{w} She's smiling, with those big round eyes open and her pristine white teeth showing."


translate English day6_cr_0bb09ea5:


    cr "I'll see you tomorrow."


translate English day6_cr_6a30f070:


    nar "I feel like she's about to leave and go away to someplace very far."


translate English day6_cr_5c73a32d:


    nar "Once again, our thoughts are the same.{w} She fled to me to escape her nevertheless hopeless family situation, and now she's about to flee FROM me."


translate English day6_cr_6b95fc61:


    nar "She's turning her back to the true feelings deep inside her that she finally confronted."


translate English day6_cr_243d7b4a:


    nar "And having realized that, she'll live a life filled with suffering, feeling like nothing is fair."


translate English day6_cr_db335bb5:


    nar "As she picks up her shoes in one hand, she makes a point of trying not to meet my eyes.{w} I can feel it. This is it."


translate English day6_cr_494fa25f:


    nar "What will I do?"


translate English day6_cr_b975ede7:


    nar "I silently gaze at Claire's back."


translate English day6_cr_1a57d51c:


    nar "As she goes down the stairs with her shoes dangling from her hand by their slender straps, the soles of her bare feet grow dark with dirt."


translate English day6_cr_858f4575:


    nar "I think to myself that it doesn't suit her.{w} She's always been so proud of her appearance."


translate English day6_cr_9a3de570:


    nar "This could have been a new start.{w} But now it's over.{w} Our relationship will go no further."


translate English day6_cr_0d2c0cf5:


    nar "But her last, clear words to me are right.{w} Tomorrow, she'll be back with a smile, talking to me about silly, inconsequential things."


translate English day6_cr_9372f53a:


    nar "Recent rumors about others, the latest capital trends, the events of the day.{w} But I'll never again be involved with her worries regarding her family and fianc."


translate English day6_cr_2b9f8979:


    nar "Our friendship won't go any further than this now."


translate English day6_cr_7737407e:


    nar "And now nothing I talked about with her over the last few days matters.{w} I'm frustrated. It makes me feel utterly powerless."


translate English day6_cr_92164e9a:


    nar "The people of the Magic Department come to mind.{w} I still haven't even found a clear answer about myself yet."


translate English day6_cr_dbb478de:


    nar "Trying to come up with solutions together about her engagement won't do anything but affect us negatively now."


translate English day6_cr_9de2909f:


    nar "I know that.{w} But it still hurts."


translate English day6_cr_61f72f71:


    nar "It's all come to nothing, but the memories will remain."


translate English day6_cr_211c58b0:


    nar "Neither of us will ever forget about it."


translate English day6_cr_dbc00f9e:


    nar "Now that we've thrown it all away, all that remains is the pain from learning firsthand truths that we didn't want to learn."


translate English day6_cr_25c89ad6:


    nar "My legs are asleep and my rear is tired from sitting on this hard floor for so long, but I still can't bring myself to go back."


translate English day6_cr_283a0b54:


    nar "I get the lonely feeling that this will be the last time I ever come back to this place."


translate English day6_cr_361e316d:


    nar "Whenever I talked with her, I forgot about my own situation."


translate English day6_cr_4f5453db:


    nar "Who do I want to become?{w} What abilities do I have?{w} Who SHOULD I become?"


translate English day6_cr_b60b934a:


    nar "I didn't have to think about any of those things. I didn't have to shoulder any of the responsibility."


translate English day6_cr_bb297df1:


    nar "But that's all in the past now."


translate English day6_cr_697cac90:


    pl "It's your fault, Claire.{w} You just had to go and get married...!"


translate English day6_cr_bb484c0f:


    nar "The words from my lips serve only to make me feel emptier."


translate English day6_cr_422c9c07:


    nar "But I said them, and I want to say more.{w} Yet I can't."


translate English day6_cr_a0a58773:


    nar "The male voice echoing through this quiet stairwell is a lot more foolish sounding than I thought it would be."


translate English day6_cr_175f5069:


    nar "I stay there for a while, then go down the stairs."


translate English day6_cr_06b65010:


    nar "A lot was on my thoughts when I went up them, but going down, nothing comes to mind."


translate English day6_cr_1b3db633:


    nar "I wonder how much time I've spent here--and how much I've wasted."


translate English day6_cr_ba81bbec:


    nar "But outside the emergency stairwell, nothing has change since I went in.{w} It feels like the time never even passed to begin with."


translate English day6_hk_ef9a2ac7:


    br "\n She's not the type of person who can erase her memories at will."


translate English day6_hk_b850219a:


    extend "\n Without clear boundaries separating memories from reality, it's impossible to be fully aware of the discomfort you bring to the world around you. "


translate English day6_hk_168b9b23:


    extend "I wonder what it's like to only have clouded memories for one or two days. "


translate English day6_hk_8ddb163d:


    extend "She loved herself, but she hardly ever talks about herself."


translate English day6_hk_827a2dfd:


    extend "\n I feel like she talked to me about her fears once."


translate English day6_hk_dea35be0:


    extend "\n I remember being exhausted from not getting enough sleep. When I came to, the bishop was smiling at me, her brows knit with worry. {w}I'd drooled on myself while unconscious."


translate English day6_hk_e3dc66a1:


    extend "\n It's not like I'd been bored or anything. {w}I'd just been too tired to stay awake."


