    br "\n For me, Gregor Cornish is a man who, frankly speaking, I want nothing to do with."


translate English day6_gr_ab4d2741:


    extend "\n He always looks tired and is always bent over at the waist, constantly reeking of the awful cigarettes he burns his lungs with, though that's not the reason why I dislike his company."


translate English day6_gr_5d38daa1:


    extend "\n Up until now, I've never found it difficult to deal with adults, assuming that you can keep them in a good mood while you do so."


translate English day6_gr_2265a00a:


    extend "\n Though I only came upon this realization for the first time in my life thanks to him."


translate English day6_gr_bbc8b8df:



    nvl clear
    br "\n No matter what I say to him, it never seems to change his mind, and he never reacts in any noticeable way. {w}That he always treats me like a child"


translate English day6_gr_40a7af2c:


    extend "\n or like an invalid patient who can't speak for themselves is, quite frankly, more than enough to leave me feeling uncomfortable."


translate English day6_gr_f3d0358b:


    extend "\n There's something to be said about indifference being far worse than outright hatred. {w}I quickly find myself feeling irate every time I'm forced to be in his presence."


translate English day6_gr_b7c5ff62:


    extend "\n To be fair, I'd be far less anxious if he was with anyone other than Dr. Grette."


translate English day6_gr_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_gr_a1a89088:


    nar "While on an aimless stroll, I naturally find myself at the infirmary. {w}I notice the light's on, but I decide to wander around a bit more instead of going straight in."


translate English day6_gr_8abe8fd0:


    nar "It's mainly because I don't want to bump into the Health Department's bishop. {w}I'm glad I can at least talk to him now, but that doesn't make our interactions any less awkward."


translate English day6_gr_9ccde2be:


    nar "I furtively peek in through the window. {w}Seeing Dr. Grette sitting at her desk like always, pen in hand, fills me with a sense of relief."


translate English day6_gr_e039a6c5:


    nar "I open the door and she turns to face me, almost like she's been waiting for me to stop by."


translate English day6_gr_1c14ab26:


    gr "Come on in, [na2]. Any reason why you felt the need to peep through the window first?"


translate English day6_gr_f53591bf:


    pl "Oops... {w}Morning, doc. I guess there's no point in pretending like I have no idea what you're talking about."


translate English day6_gr_a79567e7:


    gr "Hee hee hee! You're far too young to get anything past me, kid. {w}Besides, is this really how you want to waste your precious few days off?"


translate English day6_gr_468ad5bf:


    pl "I feel the most comfortable when I'm here, and with that in mind, I'm only a few steps away from moving in."


translate English day6_gr_af1a775e:


    gr "Mm-hm. Another day, another perfect answer! {w}Would you be a dear and entertain yourself for a moment? I'm just about done."


translate English day6_gr_97b80b3b:


    pl "I came slightly too early, huh?"


translate English day6_gr_dd7446e3:


    gr "Slightly, but that just gives us more time to spend together."


translate English day6_gr_21ac2e9f:


    pl "Your answer is just as perfect as mine."


translate English day6_gr_2d625305:


    gr "Well, of course. If there's anything you want to do, go for it."


translate English day6_gr_bf2db3bc:


    pl "Have anything for me to fidget with?"


translate English day6_gr_8d64881f:


    gr "Just hanging out is too boring for you, huh? {w}Hee hee! You're like a little kid who can't sit still for too long."


translate English day6_gr_c7a1974f:


    pl "I didn't think you'd give me permission that easily... You're a real softie when it comes to your kids, huh?"


translate English day6_gr_c13aead7:


    gr "Oh gosh! Does that mean you see yourself as a kid then?"


translate English day6_gr_d79a25b2:


    pl "I didn't mean it like that!"


translate English day6_gr_b69fe1b6:


    gr "Feel free to do whatever your heart desires."


translate English day6_gr_85ca4deb:


    pl "Come on... I'm long past the age where I need something to fiddle with."


translate English day6_gr_08e263ad:


    nar "Being here in the infirmary is relaxing."


translate English day6_gr_05446079:


    nar "The warm air, steeped with sweet smells, causes my leaden eyelids to droop, {w}and the couch is soft and comfy enough for napping."


translate English day6_gr_0de91ed5:


    nar "I yawn, feeling cozy. This spot also gives me a nice view of the doctor, who's sitting on the other side of the low table."


translate English day6_gr_5a11f7be:


    nar "I enjoy watching her sitting there on her stool, which she probably chose on purpose to make it easier for her to turn and face whoever is on the couch."


translate English day6_gr_e2f16431:


    nar "She'll occasionally bring a document closer to her face to read it easier. {w}The sound of her feet tapping against the floor and her pen scratching against paper is comforting."


translate English day6_gr_d8744f7b:


    nar "I yawn again, before noticing a box that's on the table."


translate English day6_gr_128dde52:


    nar "The handleless white box made of fairly thin cardboard looks like something used for carrying around cakes."


translate English day6_gr_fa1b0527:


    nar "Curiosity piqued, I glance over at the doctor, who's still hard at work."


translate English day6_gr_c3821b38:


    nar "I carefully open the box, which is when something black jumps up into my face. {w}It's a bug."


translate English day6_gr_c3c021cb:


    nar "I look back down into the box, wanting to know what's inside."


translate English day6_gr_727a40f1:


    nar "I spot a hunk of meat with bloody veins running through it."


translate English day6_gr_34a2c061:


    nar "This lump of flesh dripping yellowish-white fat has clearly been left here in this warm room for quite a while,"


translate English day6_gr_ce6ef54d:


    nar "considering the amount of pitch-black flies writhing all over it."


translate English day6_gr_0c10dffb:


    pl "Wh-whuh... uh... AAAAAH!!!" with sshake


translate English day6_gr_931116fd:


    nar "As the air around me quickly becomes full of flies, I belatedly realize what I'm looking at and fling the box across the room with a cry of disgust."


translate English day6_gr_6fcd05e6:


    nar "I bump into the couch behind me as I try to back away and fall down, flailing frantically in an attempt at waving off the swarm of flies."


translate English day6_gr_6f7bad75:


    gr "What's wrong?!"


translate English day6_gr_dc7938c8:


    nar "I hear the doctor's worried shout a moment later followed by the sound of her frantic footsteps, {w}and my chaotic view of the world is suddenly blocked by her body."


translate English day6_gr_23bf05ca:


    nar "I'm gradually able to slow my panicked breathing."


translate English day6_gr_2499c648:


    pl "What the heck was that, doc? Why do you even have something like that...?"


translate English day6_gr_45d1f2ba:


    gr "What are you...? {w}Oh... You mean what's inside that box?"


translate English day6_gr_53c1c7f0:


    nar "She quickly bends down to look under the table and lets out a quiet groan."


translate English day6_gr_808f97ca:


    gr "I'm so sorry. It was a bunch of old tarts that I forgot about... {w}I was planning on tossing them once I finished working."


translate English day6_gr_5ccc0885:


    pl "I'm sorry? Those were TARTS?"


translate English day6_gr_c3000590:


    gr "Yeah. I got a little carried away and made too many."


translate English day6_gr_b3a01455:


    nar "I get up from where my position on the couch and creep a little closer. {w}The mystery objects are indeed tarts. {w}Strawberry, blueberry, and all manner of berry tarts with cream."


translate English day6_gr_2f0037a9:


    nar "Tiny flies are busily buzzing around the pastries that lay crushed on the ground thanks to my panic attack."


translate English day6_gr_58716cbb:


    nar "Despite being squashed, the sight of those otherwise perfect pastries crawling with flies is somewhat shocking."


translate English day6_gr_daed9505:


    nar "Granted, that's not the only reason why I'm so shocked. {w}It happened again--another hallucination."


translate English day6_gr_1ee11c92:


    nar "I try to keep my thoughts from spiraling out of control as I watch the doctor wipe up the remainder of the tarts with a dry cloth."


translate English day6_gr_fab5a011:


    pl "I'm s-sorry... I shouldn't have opened that box..."


translate English day6_gr_4d0bb5c4:


    gr "It's my fault for leaving it on the table like that instead of throwing it out right away like I should have."


translate English day6_gr_ea99e3ad:


    gr "That gave you quite a scare, huh? Are you okay?"


translate English day6_gr_7e60accb:


    pl "Yeah... I'm fine now. I'm sorry for bothering you while you're working."


translate English day6_gr_6d91d355:


    gr "Would a glass of warm milk help?"


translate English day6_gr_742aee26:


    pl "I'm fine, r-really. I don't want to bother you anymore than I have."


translate English day6_gr_579347a7:


    gr "There's no need to feel bad, [na2]. My work isn't more important than your well being. {w}Why not sit and rest for a bit?"


translate English day6_gr_1b808355:


    nar "Still feeling skeptical, she sets a glass of warm milk down on the table for me."


translate English day6_gr_7c40d88c:


    nar "That faintly sweet, uniquely acidic dairy smell I know so well drifts up through the white steam, calming my nerves."


translate English day6_gr_e3d2b9ca:


    pl "Thanks..."


translate English day6_gr_d1670f38:


    gr "For what? This is the least I can do."


translate English day6_gr_c6b2eee6:


    pl "I had no idea flies liked cake that much."


translate English day6_gr_964d97d8:


    gr "Flies tend to gravitate toward anything that was once alive."


translate English day6_gr_b13efee7:


    gr "All manner of sweets are made from ingredients that come from animals that were once alive, which is why even flies enjoy them. {w}Kind of like how fruit flies love fruit."


translate English day6_gr_8a08639c:


    pl "I see..."


translate English day6_gr_dd5a05a3:


    gr "Can I ask you something, [na2]?"


translate English day6_gr_7631af35:


    pl "What's that?"


translate English day6_gr_d88619ef:


    gr "Did you see something else when you opened that box?"


translate English day6_gr_d2cb3908:


    pl "Something else...? Well..."


translate English day6_gr_85f7236a:


    gr "I'm your doctor, [na2]. {w}I can't help you if you don't open up to me about what's bothering you."


translate English day6_gr_cde2c55b:


    nar "The word \"doctor\" never held any special significance until now, though I'm starting to suspect it's taken on a certain weight recently."


translate English day6_gr_7c54954d:


    pl "I saw something slightly bizarre, almost like a chunk of meat... {w}Maybe because of the strawberries."


translate English day6_gr_18fec3d3:


    pl "But you know what they say, doc. You tend to see what you're used to."


translate English day6_gr_c00dbec6:


    pl "My job is disposing of dead bodies, so I'm used to seeing that kind of stuff in my daily life..."


translate English day6_gr_07acc9a9:


    pl "Also, to be fair, I might have dozed off a bit. {w}I'm sure it was all a product of my still half-asleep mind."


translate English day6_gr_c79cb1a4:


    gr "Mm, I understand what you're saying, [na2]. I've been there."


translate English day6_gr_32243ee6:


    gr "This room does have a lulling effect, doesn't it? {w}Should I open a window and get some fresh air in?"


translate English day6_gr_5fc9bfe0:


    pl "Uh... Sure. Thanks..."


translate English day6_gr_571745d5:


    nar "I nod, acting like everything's fine, though I'm growing progressively annoyed that she changed the subject."


translate English day6_gr_2eaafbe4:


    nar "Did she just look at me like I'm some kind of lunatic? {w}What did I just say? {w}Nothing too weird, I hope..."


translate English day6_gr_92a474fc:


    gr "The temple air is usually quite fresh, with only the infirmary being oddly warm. Weird, huh?"


translate English day6_gr_cfcc8193:


    gr "Some people like it. I personally don't mind..."


translate English day6_gr_187c689d:


    gr "But like you just said, [na2], it definitely makes me sleepy, which can be problematic."


translate English day6_gr_db80ed84:


    pl "Right? I know how that is."


translate English day6_gr_6d258acc:


    gr "Honestly, I'm starting to feel a little drowsy myself. {w}How about we chat for a bit?"


translate English day6_gr_1099bd99:


    pl "I'm fine, and you have work to finish..."


translate English day6_gr_3000ac16:


    gr "There's no way I'll get anything done in this state,"


translate English day6_gr_af94b87a:


    gr "and besides, it's pretty impolite sitting here with my back to a guest, leaving him to entertain himself while I focus on other matters."


translate English day6_gr_7369c2b0:


    pl "Haha... It's very like you to think that way."


translate English day6_gr_38d252c1:


    gr "I'd love to chat with you while we snack on some sweets... {w}but unfortunately, I didn't bake anything for today. Hrm... What should we do...?"


translate English day6_gr_f67f4656:


    pl "Please, don't go out of your way for me. {w}I'm honestly grateful for everything you've given me so far..."


translate English day6_gr_31288b04:


    pl "One of these days I'll take over the kitchen and make you something delicious."


translate English day6_gr_38f1849e:


    gr "Really? You know how to bake, [na2]?"


translate English day6_gr_3c7fde4c:


    pl "Of course. I can handle anything that involves fire in the creation process, and baking requires plenty of it."


translate English day6_gr_b9c18b92:


    gr "How wonderful! Granted, I expected no less from you, [na2]. A boy who knows his way around a kitchen must be very popular among the ladies."


translate English day6_gr_ef89b336:


    pl "Heh... I've never baked pastries, though. {w}Mainly because sweets aren't really my thing... So maybe you can give me a couple pointers?"


translate English day6_gr_443113e1:


    gr "I was hoping a day like this might come, though I honestly never thought it really would. I'd be more than happy to help!"


translate English day6_gr_0e40770d:


    pl "You're definitely more like a teacher than a doctor when you're teaching something."


translate English day6_gr_600175cc:


    gr "To tell you the truth, I'm only really good at baking. {w}I have zero confidence in my cooking skills, embarrassingly enough..."


translate English day6_gr_adcb93ee:


    pl "Seriously? That's surprising..."


translate English day6_gr_f0f3d121:


    gr "Yeah... Ever since I was a young girl, I always just figured I'd never get the chance to cook for someone else."


translate English day6_gr_12784d4a:


    pl "Because of your values?"


translate English day6_gr_098fb36e:


    gr "Ha, because I never saw myself ever getting married. {w}You see, I had a little accident."


translate English day6_gr_64317db0:


    pl "What happened?"


translate English day6_gr_ec09d032:


    gr "Well... I'm kind of embarrassed suddenly turning the topic of our conversation onto myself..."


translate English day6_gr_c4446dcb:


    gr "But when I was much younger, I was involved in a Pestis-related incident."


translate English day6_gr_4466dbfb:


    gr "I came out of it mostly okay, but unfortunately with some lingering side-effects."


translate English day6_gr_f6ca4bcd:


    gr "It's what led to my current infertility... {w}Basically, my body is incapable of bearing children."


translate English day6_gr_c4255f2c:


    gr "I also stopped growing, which is why I'm stuck with the height of a small child..."


translate English day6_gr_a0e47f55:


    pl "I'm sorry..."


translate English day6_gr_82142f0e:


    gr "Oh! I'm completely fine with it now!"


translate English day6_gr_772265ec:


    gr "The treatment I received got rid of most of my pain and being able to run around like the other kids made me forget all about it."


translate English day6_gr_5bf8f48d:


    gr "But my parents were pretty heartbroken about it. They loved me so much..."


translate English day6_gr_2c83bcbe:


    gr "From that day forward, my mother would take my hand every night before bed and pray for me. I still remember the way she looked at me..."


translate English day6_gr_f262f390:


    gr "I hated the pity I saw in her eyes so much that I remember telling her once how I didn't need a husband in order to be happy. Shouting that I could easily do without..."


translate English day6_gr_2d7675e3:


    gr "...Which only made her sadder."


translate English day6_gr_8cfc4001:


    pl "How did you end up getting married then?"


translate English day6_gr_56553c62:


    nar "My words seem to rekindle a fire in her eyes that had died down while talking to me. {w}I'm starting to feel uncomfortable again."


translate English day6_gr_5e54bed7:


    gr "Well... {w}Because I knew that he was my soulmate the first time I laid eyes on him!"


translate English day6_gr_7650ec29:


    gr "That would be a pretty magical reason, right? The truth is it took a fairly long time to reach the point of marriage."


translate English day6_gr_b8a25ae5:


    gr "The thing about him is he lacked a certain degree of...fortitude."


translate English day6_gr_6db8dd7c:


    gr "I was something of a wild-child at the time and didn't see him as a potential partner. {w}But then, one day..."


translate English day6_gr_aaab2dfb:


    gr "Sometime around my coming of age ceremony, I think? {w}He finally told me how he felt about me and I was completely blindsided considering he'd been fairly unfriendly until then."


translate English day6_gr_e9453b50:


    gr "But he seemed to take me seriously, which made me really happy..."


translate English day6_gr_0919a3a1:


    pl "You've been together since your coming of age ceremony? That's quite a long relationship."


translate English day6_gr_2b2dee96:


    gr "But it was far from the fairytale romance I grew up reading about."


translate English day6_gr_9176212f:


    gr "I ended up leaving the capital around the time he entered the temple. I wanted to study more, broaden my horizons."


translate English day6_gr_4f7e6540:


    gr "Communication between the temple and the outside world is difficult, and our relationship fell to the wayside due to just how busy we both were."


translate English day6_gr_d3bdf3d3:


    gr "Years passed before we were eventually reunited. {w}Remember that girl I mentioned before?"


translate English day6_gr_ca71439e:


    pl "You mean your first patient after becoming a doctor?"


translate English day6_gr_00c6091b:


    gr "Yes, exactly."


translate English day6_gr_91d5fbcd:


    gr "He's the one who first introduced me to her--which is actually how we got back in touch."


translate English day6_gr_965573d0:


    gr "As for our marriage... {w}I originally never planned on doing so... But for better or worse, he was promoted to the role of Bishop on the 7th of the month."


translate English day6_gr_ebf799ad:


    gr "I couldn't leave after that."


translate English day6_gr_490d0274:


    gr "It was around the second time I ended up stuck on the receiving end of his long-winded rants."


translate English day6_gr_8b726903:


    gr "Which is what ultimately led me to being here."


translate English day6_gr_44e0307b:


    pl "Wow, so that's the reason why you came here? You're a tough customer, doc."


translate English day6_gr_45b8a5dc:


    gr "Heh... Despite being quite young at the time, I was still old enough to know how difficult it was to throw yourself into a new challenge without giving it the proper amount of thought."


translate English day6_gr_338f7a96:


    gr "A part of me didn't think it would be so bad to spend the rest of my life with him."


translate English day6_gr_757c9db1:


    gr "If you stay at this job long enough, there will almost certainly come a time when you need someone by your side."


translate English day6_gr_04f38680:


    gr "I know that's not very romantic, but I have no regrets about choosing him to be my life partner."


translate English day6_gr_eb1e660c:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_d4ca4312:


    gr "Ha ha ha! Rambling on and on about myself is really embarrassing! {w}The moral of the story is not that you should live your life and get married..."


translate English day6_gr_7423fbdc:


    gr "But I am saying that having a life-partner isn't necessarily a bad thing."


translate English day6_gr_85e015df:


    gr "And you don't always need a melodramatic reason for whoever you end up with."


translate English day6_gr_69ee5c8d:


    gr "Okay, I'm done! {w}Did I clear up any doubts you once had?"


translate English day6_gr_428a7687:


    pl "Yes, spectacularly. {w}I always love listening to you talk."


translate English day6_gr_9a03e458:


    pl "You mentioned you left the capital to study?"


translate English day6_gr_5112c16e:


    pl "If I ever get the chance to leave this place, I'd love traveling around like you did, bouncing from place to place."


translate English day6_gr_ab1ec424:


    gr "Knowing your love of freedom, [na2], I think that type of lifestyle would suit you well."


translate English day6_gr_758189d8:


    gr "Is there anything you want to study, or any place you want to visit?"


translate English day6_gr_047f7fce:


    pl "Not really..."


translate English day6_gr_45514f8c:


    pl "I have a friend who really loves flowers and animals. {w}I don't necessarily share their enthusiasm, though..."


translate English day6_gr_6b12c935:


    pl "But I know it would make her happy if I knew all about the stuff she's into. {w}Well... It's not like I'll ever get out of here."


translate English day6_gr_55eec4cc:


    gr "I think that's a marvelous reason for doing something. {w}Sometimes doing something for other people in our lives leads to bettering ourselves in the process."


translate English day6_gr_e2137b2c:


    gr "For example, I'm always thinking about what things you like to eat and what you might hate."


translate English day6_gr_4b5de44c:


    gr "You're not a huge fan of wildlife then [na2]?"


translate English day6_gr_2d5d9be8:


    pl "Like I said, I don't hate it. I love looking at animals and plants, but it's just..."


translate English day6_gr_d775ff21:


    pl "Maybe it's due to never being given much responsibility growing up, {w}but I kind of hate the feeling that some living creature's life is in my hands..."


translate English day6_gr_77370324:


    gr "Yeah? And yet you come off as a very dependable person, a strong boy who always thinks about the people around him."


translate English day6_gr_62798755:


    pl "That's only how I act in front of you..."


translate English day6_gr_d624ad0b:


    gr "Then if I'm always watching, you'll always have to be a good kid!"


translate English day6_gr_a1cc9b33:


    pl "Doc... I'm really happy to hear you say that, but I wish you wouldn't treat me like a kid all the time."


translate English day6_gr_d185eace:


    pl "I may look like one, but my efforts are far beyond what a child could do."


translate English day6_gr_b4591416:


    gr "Oh gosh... I'm sorry. I never meant to make you feel bad."


translate English day6_gr_f66c74ab:


    gr "It's kind of a bad habit of mine... I've had other folks tell me the same thing from time to time, and yet I still can't help myself..."


translate English day6_gr_af7e38c3:


    pl "What about you, doc? You seem like the type of person who enjoys taking care of plants and animals."


translate English day6_gr_428d6ad4:


    gr "Me? {w}Well...now that I think about it, I'm not sure I've ever had the chance to take care of a pet or a plant."


translate English day6_gr_6240ec21:


    gr "I do enjoy watching them from afar... I guess my hands are full enough looking after the priests here in the temple."


translate English day6_gr_65ac33de:


    pl "You're kind of a chicken when it comes to certain things, doc."


translate English day6_gr_d52e089a:


    gr "Ngh... You didn't have to agree with me so quickly."


translate English day6_gr_ba7873a1:


    gr "Just watching them is good enough for me."


translate English day6_gr_b7535688:


    gr "When I see them, it reminds me of how precious each gift of life is and other stuff like that..."


translate English day6_gr_2736fc8f:


    gr "On the other hand, Evelynn is very much into raising both animals and plants!"


translate English day6_gr_7d85d520:


    gr "I've had many opportunities to enjoy the fruits of her labor."


translate English day6_gr_15380b45:


    pl "You mean the bishop of the Academics Department?"


translate English day6_gr_61fc2fe5:


    gr "Yes. The forest around the temple is actually maintained by the Academics Department. Did you know that?"


translate English day6_gr_5d9a2def:


    pl "I didn't, but somehow, that job does seem to suit her..."


translate English day6_gr_b322acaa:


    gr "Evelynn is truly an amazing person. I've thought so ever since we were young."


translate English day6_gr_2e2c57d4:


    gr "She can make any animal instantly fall in love with her, and there's nothing she doesn't know when it comes to flowers, trees...even roadside weeds!"


translate English day6_gr_5131b3b8:


    gr "Sometimes I find myself wishing I could be even half as amazing as she is..."


translate English day6_gr_821790db:


    pl "I think you're already pretty amazing in your own right, doc. {w}Everyone who meets you absolutely adores you and you're a fountain of information regarding the temple, not to mention the capital."


translate English day6_gr_e455c68f:


    pl "I wish I could be like you, doc."


translate English day6_gr_5966b22c:


    gr "I swear I wasn't fishing for compliments, but thanks all the same."


translate English day6_gr_e1c82694:


    gr "Hearing you say that makes me really happy."


translate English day6_gr_5c863e1a:


    pl "Why wouldn't I? I love that you're always so willing to chat with me whenever you have a moment to spare."


translate English day6_gr_a7ef18cb:


    gr "Is that a compliment? I'll take it as one anyways."


translate English day6_gr_fdc2939e:


    gr "It's starting to get a bit cold in here. Mind if I close the window?"


translate English day6_gr_dcb29cce:


    pl "Whatever you want."


translate English day6_gr_b614d0c5:


    nar "Time passes as we engage in our usual chit-chat. {w}So much so that I soon forget what happened earlier."


translate English day6_gr_3b568fda:


    nar "And yet I still can't shake my sense of unease, {w}even though there's no reason for me to feel that way."


translate English day6_gr_2c51b130:


    pl "Is the infirmary usually this quiet?"


translate English day6_gr_80da2994:


    gr "Not all the time, no."


translate English day6_gr_5d3128b2:


    gr "But with that said, this time of day is usually fairly quiet, probably because everyone's busy working."


translate English day6_gr_7d90b81e:


    gr "I tend to use my mornings for getting paperwork done, leaving my afternoons free for my hospital rounds."


translate English day6_gr_6e621021:


    pl "Hmm... I was wondering why I never seem to see anyone here when I stop by."


translate English day6_gr_46eba165:


    gr "On the plus side, it gives me more time to talk with you, [na2]."


translate English day6_gr_40061891:


    pl "And I get you all to myself!"


translate English day6_gr_83ab4969:


    gr "When we do get around to baking something together, we should definitely make sure to take a photo for the album."


translate English day6_gr_14be2141:


    pl "Yeah... That's a good idea. You still have that camera?"


translate English day6_gr_53e4994d:


    gr "Of course. Want me to get it?"


translate English day6_gr_a69689df:


    pl "There's not really anything I want to take a photo of right now."


translate English day6_gr_d8cb53dd:


    nar "When I'd held it the other day, it felt like a normal sized device, but seeing it in her hands makes it seem slightly bigger than I remember."


translate English day6_gr_bc9b8848:


    nar "She handles it with an ease that comes with experience, and as she points the camera in my direction, one eye closed, {w}I find myself forcing a ridiculously unnatural smile on my face."


translate English day6_gr_291a4925:


    pl "That camera's pretty old, huh?"


translate English day6_gr_2cdb36fe:


    gr "Yeah. I've had it since I was a student."


translate English day6_gr_c4dd65e1:


    gr "How about a cool pose, kid?"


translate English day6_gr_8e10af7f:


    pl "That's okay. I'm embarrassed enough!"


translate English day6_gr_335b01d4:


    gr "Why? You're so photogenic, you'd look good from any angle."


translate English day6_gr_27ac47a7:


    pl "I'm well aware! I'm just not in the mood... And a picture tends to reflect how a person is truly feeling, right?"


translate English day6_gr_a0c7a3b5:


    gr "Does that mean there's a problem you still haven't told me about?"


translate English day6_gr_73338b7e:


    nar "I find myself shuffling awkwardly under her direct gaze as opposed to when her attention was focused on the lens."


translate English day6_gr_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_311e6761:


    gr "Remember what I mentioned yesterday? I wish you'd tell me if something's bothering you."


translate English day6_gr_136ccee6:


    nar "My lips, unable to speak, twitch almost nervously. I've managed to stumble into the exact situation I was most afraid of."


translate English day6_gr_5efcea5e:


    nar "I've managed to avoid it this long, but now there's no way out."


translate English day6_gr_86e44b8f:


    nar "This situation will only repeat itself until I offer a satisfactory answer."


translate English day6_gr_416cb16c:


    nar "And the thought of being forced to face her like this until that happens makes my head hurt."


translate English day6_gr_a4356cd9:


    nar "What if the words that come out of my mouth end up being incomprehensible?"


translate English day6_gr_aa6f93f1:


    nar "Words I'll have to repeat and those I can never take back... {w}My chaotic thoughts are quickly spiraling into worst case scenarios."


translate English day6_gr_a7798bd5:


    gr "[na2]."


translate English day6_gr_f1c08faa:


    nar "Her kind voice immediately unravels my tangled thoughts while smoothing my furrowed brow. {w}It's a voice that's become quite familiar to me."


translate English day6_gr_518db615:


    nar "She wants a serious answer from me, and I know that she'll listen to whatever I tell her with thoughtful earnestness."


translate English day6_gr_cdd83c41:


    nar "But it will also plant seeds of doubt in her mind. {w}And that's the last thing I want."


translate English day6_gr_9148e2d9:


    nar "I don't want her to view me as that kind of patient."


translate English day6_gr_48b201c5:


    nar "But I'm kind of trapped now. I should simply stop fighting my fear of staying silent and let her figure out what's wrong with me."


translate English day6_gr_ac2bcc6c:


    nar "Honestly, I'd be lying if I said I hadn't considered that option more than once."


translate English day6_gr_7eb26890:


    nar "But what if, even after confiding in her, my problem doesn't get better?"


translate English day6_gr_c6108dce:


    pl "Actually..."


translate English day6_gr_709ede3e:


    gr "Yes?"


translate English day6_gr_d99b0fb5:


    nar "I pause again. {w}The pads of my fingers cling to the side of the now cold milk cup as my breathing grows shaky and unsteady."


translate English day6_gr_67e2b0a0:


    nar "I start coughing for no reason. {w}I should probably get my thoughts in some kind of order."


translate English day6_gr_c6b314d0:


    nar "The thing that's tortured me the most, that I've found to be the most bizarre... {w}That thing is..."


translate English day6_gr_ca33e87e:


    pl "I've been having this weird dream lately..."


translate English day6_gr_16df32b4:


    gr "A weird dream?"


translate English day6_gr_23166958:


    pl "Yeah. At first, I wrote it off as just your typical nightmare. {w}But then it kept repeating every night when I closed my eyes."


translate English day6_gr_346b7f21:


    pl "And despite the vividly phantasmagorical landscape, it almost feels like a memory of something I've experienced first-hand..."


translate English day6_gr_e78b5b50:


    gr "Can you tell me what the dream is about?"


translate English day6_gr_f7019f45:


    pl "It's always the same."


translate English day6_gr_c2969198:


    pl "I'm standing alone under a red sky, and stuffed among the animal entrails scattered around me are human corpses."


translate English day6_gr_91a4d36e:


    pl "They're never bodies of people I know, but I can see them well enough to recognize them for what they are-corpses."


translate English day6_gr_a425dcfa:


    gr "Then what happens?"


translate English day6_gr_33a2d2e4:


    pl "Then the cloudy sky opens up and light shines down. {w}Intense pain rips through my stomach every time I see it."


translate English day6_gr_0cc0482b:


    pl "Not because of the light itself, but because of the angel."


translate English day6_gr_fa670b66:


    pl "You know what an angel is, right, doc? {w}Have you ever seen one in real life?"


translate English day6_gr_b8513128:


    pl "I have no idea how angels are depicted in the capital, but in my dream, she's a woman."


translate English day6_gr_dfd606b9:


    pl "And she has these dazzlingly, pure-white wings, which are the source of the light."


translate English day6_gr_f934b221:


    pl "I know that, at the end of the day, it's just a dream, an image concocted by my own mind... but she's so beautiful. {w}I can sense a warmth and kindness in her."


translate English day6_gr_542534cd:


    pl "But that's it because I can't touch her..."


translate English day6_gr_4170a21e:


    gr "Have you had similar dreams before?"


translate English day6_gr_8ccb406d:


    pl "No... I only had normal dreams for the first few days after arriving here."


translate English day6_gr_cccb344c:


    pl "The angel started appearing in my dreams... {w}Let me think. Today marks my sixth day here, meaning... it'd been three or four days since I'd arrived."


translate English day6_gr_7db54aec:


    nar "The doctor listens intently to every word I say, a grim expression on her face. {w}She closes her eyes for a moment, as if thinking about something, before opening them again."


translate English day6_gr_bacd4f9c:


    gr "Didn't you mention something about experiencing hallucinations and memory loss about three days ago, [na2]?"


translate English day6_gr_d489ad14:


    gr "Is that also the same day you started seeing this dream?"


translate English day6_gr_c7c96b87:


    pl "Yeah... You might be right..."


translate English day6_gr_1992f51b:


    gr "What exactly does this angel look like? Is she a child? {w}Or an adult?"


translate English day6_gr_be8c6e49:


    pl "She's... {w}Actually, I can't remember, but she always wants to touch me in some way. {w}To hold my hand or to embrace me in her arms..."


translate English day6_gr_5c7307be:


    pl "And every time she does, the feeling is revolting. It fills me with disgust..."


translate English day6_gr_8973ccc8:


    gr "And then?"


translate English day6_gr_eb1e660c_2:


    pl "..."


translate English day6_gr_79bdc8d9:


    nar "Once again finding it difficult to continue, I take a deep breath in."


translate English day6_gr_efb92329:


    nar "This time, it's more than simple embarrassment that makes it difficult for me to continue talking about my bizarre experience."


translate English day6_gr_ac34c57e:


    nar "I'm legitimately afraid."


translate English day6_gr_ad9d704b:


    nar "It's a reaction I can offer no rational explanation for, which only further fuels my irrational fear, making it grow in intensity."


translate English day6_gr_c05a3e1c:


    nar "When I finally open my mouth to continue, my lips are parched and dry."


translate English day6_gr_7b14084b:


    pl "I know this sounds crazy... {w}but I have the feeling I've seen this angel somewhere before."


translate English day6_gr_a9a9f2cb:


    pl "And I don't mean in another dream or anything like that..."


translate English day6_gr_2f86d265:


    pl "I think she looks like someone I know in real life. {w}I have no idea who it might be..."


translate English day6_gr_f9213567:


    pl "But I'm pretty sure it's someone I'm close with."


translate English day6_gr_cba3f15c:


    pl "It could be someone who's watching over me right this very moment, which...trust me...I know how ridiculous that sounds! {w}I'm well aware, and yet...!"


translate English day6_gr_e05808c2:


    gr "Calm down, [na2]. {w}I don't think it's ridiculous at all."


translate English day6_gr_bc8693df:


    gr "If that's how you feel, then who am I to judge? {w}Think you can keep going?"


translate English day6_gr_d8d53cf0:


    pl "\"*sigh*... Okay... {w}At any rate, if this angel really is someone I know, then there must be a reason why she keeps appearing in my dreams."


translate English day6_gr_181a1ef0:


    pl "It feels less like I'm dreaming about her, and more that she's literally visiting my dreams every night."


translate English day6_gr_8694c9ad:


    pl "Is she trying to tell me something? {w}Or maybe something she wants from me?"


translate English day6_gr_2c107482:


    gr "And you have absolutely no idea who she might be? Not even a single clue?"


translate English day6_gr_8172ffed:


    pl "Well...no. {w}I have an idea of who it might be. {w}Not enough to prove definitively which is what scares me..."


translate English day6_gr_fedde20b:


    gr "Can you tell me who you think it might be, even just briefly? {w}What's something about them that stands out in your memory?"


translate English day6_gr_e2afe00b:


    pl "She's always so negative and a big crybaby...but she's equally as kind."


translate English day6_gr_ebbe4669:


    pl "We spend most of our time together, and yet she almost never talks about herself,{w} meaning I have no idea where she goes or what she spends her time doing."


translate English day6_gr_0c1608a5:


    pl "It's not that she doesn't answer the questions I ask her... {w}but more like she seems to have a hard time expressing herself properly."


translate English day6_gr_50e0f129:


    pl "That's the feeling I always get from her. {w}She has a hard time getting along with people and yet always needs someone. All she ever does is apologize..."


translate English day6_gr_a34cb542:


    pl "And it seems like she really does need help. {w}I've gone out of my way to do whatever I can, to always be there by her side..."


translate English day6_gr_7064d682:


    gr "Yeah? In that case, maybe this girl really is your angel, [na2]."


translate English day6_gr_d5b9d6bd:


    gr "There's a chance she shows up in your dreams every night because she wants to tell you something."


translate English day6_gr_33a26e9a:


    pl "But what could it be?"


translate English day6_gr_56456189:


    gr "That's something you'll have to ask her directly. {w}Assuming you think she might really be the one."


translate English day6_gr_4078bf7b:


    pl "Ask her, huh...? *sigh*... {w}Sorry for bringing up such a weird topic, doc..."


translate English day6_gr_452eb393:


    gr "Do you feel a little better?"


translate English day6_gr_3f7dc588:


    pl "I'm not sure yet, but it helped get my thoughts straight at least... {w}What do you usually dream about, doc?"


translate English day6_gr_b673aa2f:


    gr "Not anything that interesting, honestly."


translate English day6_gr_705785e6:


    pl "Tell me anyway? I don't care how boring you might think it is."


translate English day6_gr_6b982545:


    gr "Well... Lately, I feel like I've been dreaming a lot about my past experiences. {w}Especially from my time back in university."


translate English day6_gr_59c3e83d:


    gr "I'm the kind of person who doesn't realize I'm dreaming until I wake up, at which time I immediately forget everything."


translate English day6_gr_a470c305:


    gr "I mentioned it before, but I really was kind of a wild child growing up."


translate English day6_gr_70c5ba36:


    gr "I kept my hair short and I didn't wear skirts or anything girly like that."


translate English day6_gr_89ba7e9b:


    gr "I'd get in trouble a lot for dropping bowls and stuff in the mud... Heh heh heh!"


translate English day6_gr_c241ea73:


    pl "Yeah? I'd love to hear more about that time of your life."


translate English day6_gr_6572ed47:


    gr "Of course, if it makes you feel better. I'm glad I can help you, [na2], even if just a little."


translate English day6_gr_b48f983d:


    nar "She gets up from the couch before sitting at her desk."


translate English day6_gr_a8c5b41e:


    nar "Assuming she's about to return to her paperwork, {w}she pulls out a folder from a drawer in her desk instead before writing something on it with a pen."


translate English day6_gr_b3f83bc6:


    gr "Listen to me very carefully, [na2]."


translate English day6_gr_1dc2ca6f:


    pl "...?"


translate English day6_gr_0d7a079a:


    gr "The symptoms you're experiencing can all be chalked up to an acute stress reaction."


translate English day6_gr_d1f9d024:


    gr "It's a common issue among priests who work in the Cleanup Department."


translate English day6_gr_4dc050a2:


    gr "This stress tends to present through memory loss and confusion, nightmares, mild delusions, and headaches combined with auditory hallucinations. {w}I promise it's not that serious."


translate English day6_gr_ee01a042:


    gr "And treatment is incredibly simple. Try to get seven to ten hours of sleep every night and make sure to eat three meals a day."


translate English day6_gr_5ba07bd2:


    gr "Drink lots of water and eat lots of veggies."


translate English day6_gr_241b1f52:


    pl "Huh? That's all I need to do for my symptoms to go away?"


translate English day6_gr_e52b672b:


    gr "Of course! First of all, you're not sick with anything. {w}It's something anyone can experience if their stress gets bad enough."


translate English day6_gr_0d8ecc95:


    gr "You've gone through a lot recently, right? {w}Come see me again if you continue having problems sleeping or eating."


translate English day6_gr_57de9029:


    pl "I see... So I'm not sick."


translate English day6_gr_4900919d:


    nar "What really made me feel better was her emphasis on the fact that what I'm experiencing is completely normal for someone in my position."


translate English day6_gr_1766a2b7:


    nar "I'd been worried about how she might react, driving myself crazy over every possible scenario over multitudes of unseen yet potential timelines,"


translate English day6_gr_75bf1e21:


    nar "and yet the smile on her face seems as light and cheerful as always, leading me to realize how irrational my fears truly were."


translate English day6_gr_b9dc117a:


    gr "Can you promise me that you'll try to follow your doctor's orders?"


translate English day6_gr_9c44cb86:


    pl "As much as possible. Thanks for everything, doc."


translate English day6_gr_e8c0bf40:


    gr "For what? I'm just doing my job. {w}I am the resident doctor, after all."


translate English day6_ar_1fcb2444:


    br "\n Every day, she worries about the safety of others--a saint who wants to lend her ear to as many as she can.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_ar_57673bcc:


    extend "\n But she doesn't know what's happening outside of her own perspective.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_ar_db6dd0c8:


    extend "\n That's because many priests have worked hard to prevent her pure ears and eyes from being sullied.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_ar_8130cfbd:


    extend "\n That hard work has served to narrow her world even more.{w} She didn't even know about the incident within the Cleanup Department after my joining.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_ar_d412585b:


    extend "\n I have mixed feelings about it.{w} On one hand, I don't want to tell her about something so gruesome either.{w} But she'll learn about it soon enough, won't she?{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_ar_8701291d:


    extend "\n She's smart, and deeply thoughtful.{w} One day, she'll realize what it is.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_ar_140fd307:



    nvl clear
    br "\n For a long time, I was scared of that.{w} Lately, though, I've felt a stranger emotion: curiosity.{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_ar_1f53b688:


    extend "\n If she learned about everything, would she still accept me with those pure, honest eyes of hers?{w}{nw}"


translate English day6_ar_ccf5f782:


    extend "\n If she does accept me, should I get on my knees like a man in the Bible first seeing God and kiss her on the back of the hand as a show of respect and reverence?"


translate English day6_ar_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_ar_24bafe34:


    nar "Here I am, in front of the Magic Department.{w} The doors are closed, though, probably because of how early I am.{w} I'm not sure what to do."


translate English day6_ar_79cd35e8:


    nar "Everyone else is probably still at work. The priests of this department are basically always busy."


translate English day6_ar_49266d85:


    nar "Either everyone's going to be inside, or nobody is--no in-between."


translate English day6_ar_a6d27bd3:


    nar "I hesitantly enter the training grounds, which are relatively quiet but not empty."


translate English day6_ar_65b80ed2:


    nar "Right away, I hear feet hit the floor and people shout as if striking.{w} Those noises quickly grow muffled, though, not echoing well in these huge grounds."


translate English day6_ar_b7dc3ee7:


    nar "I hear the voices a second time, then a third."


translate English day6_ar_f8c6dcf8:


    nar "Arnie stands off to the side, watching over the three or four priests causing the noise.{w} She must be focused on judging their movements."


translate English day6_ar_cc808646:


    nar "At first she simply looks with arms folded, but she quickly spots me.{w} She gives a start."


translate English day6_ar_80e74d3e:


    ar "Brother [na2]?{w} What brings you here so early?"


translate English day6_ar_a3bb91e0:


    pl "I guess you could say work finished a little early today..."


translate English day6_ar_97bae1e5:


    pl "I got into that accident yesterday, remember?{w} They gave me the day off because of it."


translate English day6_ar_2f9df36c:


    ar "I see...{w} Are you well enough to be up and about?{w} You were injured..."


translate English day6_ar_b99b979e:


    pl "You saw me yesterday, right? Totally fine here.{w} I kind of feel bad for taking the day off."


translate English day6_ar_667f86a0:


    ar "I'm relieved to hear it wasn't too much of a shock for you."


translate English day6_ar_a59cbc04:


    pl "What are you doing this early in the morning, Arnie?"


translate English day6_ar_46d1c1a7:


    ar "I'm giving private lessons to the priests."


translate English day6_ar_67f658dd:


    ar "The Magic Department places great emphasis on working as a group.{w} Sometimes, as you can see, a few priests have lower morale or issues of that nature."


translate English day6_ar_e8261d23:


    ar "That causes their movements to grow sloppy, so I prioritize training them."


translate English day6_ar_3ec92695:


    pl "What? But isn't everyone supposed to be working right now?"


translate English day6_ar_fcd45076:


    ar "Improving oneself is even more vital than carrying out one's duties.{w} We devote ourselves to making a better world by helping others."


translate English day6_ar_5e519644:


    ar "To that end, we first need to train our bodies to be in the best shape they can be."


translate English day6_ar_7aa77dda:


    ar "Other priests help me in this regard as well."


translate English day6_ar_f1817f4b:


    pl "Huh..."


translate English day6_ar_78e7a745:


    nar "I couldn't help the \"huh,\" thinking about what it's like in the disposal team."


translate English day6_ar_9ab5f747:


    pl "Well, I wish the Cleanup Department priests would borrow that mindset.{w} The whole thing about helping others, anyway."


translate English day6_ar_9388796d:


    ar "Are you not already helping me, Brother?"


translate English day6_ar_fcefd1c7:


    pl "Er, well... Maybe, but what's the point if I'm the only one helping someone?"


translate English day6_ar_21ba7608:


    ar "All things must begin somewhere."


translate English day6_ar_45fe3c33:


    ar "If you wish it, and you hold that mindset close to your heart, I'm certain the others will come to understand you."


translate English day6_ar_c6c1765f:


    pl "What I mean is, that's the exact mindset I wish I had..."


translate English day6_ar_91311173:


    nar "The scattered priests form a slightly less scattered group and lower their heads to me."


translate English day6_ar_a01e87a7:


    nar "At first I always mistrusted the way they greeted me, but now that I know more of what's going on, it's not that strange to see."


translate English day6_ar_b091c324:


    nar "They heard later on that I was Arne Alternata's betrothed, so they started being more polite with me."


translate English day6_ar_c4867019:


    nar "Nevertheless, that equates to rebellion against mage history--against their own families and clans."


translate English day6_ar_606ea7f6:


    nar "The fact that they're not openly displaying their hostility towards me probably has a lot to do not only with their bishop's superior abilities, but with her benevolence as well."


translate English day6_ar_9b056a07:


    pl "...Anyway, I should get going.{w} Don't want to interrupt everyone."


translate English day6_ar_cdbaf131:


    ar "Oh!{w} Actually, would you mind waiting a short while?"


translate English day6_ar_508c333b:


    pl "Hm?"


translate English day6_ar_1535b5d6:


    ar "Your attire.{w} That isn't what you normally wear, is it?"


translate English day6_ar_17564c62:


    pl "Guess not... Well, after what happened yesterday...{w} Do you have my clothes?"


translate English day6_ar_46be157a:


    ar "I do indeed--and they've been washed and cleaned."


translate English day6_ar_1d685f13:


    ar "So...{w} If it's all the same to you, would you mind waiting a little while? Just until training is over."


translate English day6_ar_0bb1994f:


    pl "Hmm... Well, I won't have many more days to wear those clothes anyway, so..."


translate English day6_ar_f64466f1:


    ar "......"


translate English day6_ar_751e43b5:


    pl "But I'd still feel weird standing around doing nothing.{w} Will it be over soon?"


translate English day6_ar_3ccc2ee3:


    ar "Yes. Our pace is excellent this morning, so I don't believe you'll need to wait for very long."


translate English day6_ar_afceaeb1:


    pl "Alright, then do your best! I'll be rooting for you."


translate English day6_ar_e35c6a09:


    ar "Very well!"


translate English day6_ar_79346de3:


    nar "Setting her gallant answer aside, I take up a position along the wall.{w} It actually takes a good while to walk to the wall--the training grounds are just that big."


translate English day6_ar_d5a8419e:


    nar "As I lean my back up against the chilly wall, I feel the strength slowly draining from my legs."


translate English day6_ar_c8659284:


    nar "A cool wind blows in from the large windows.{w} The priests' short cries and shouts sound so distant now."


translate English day6_ar_1e03ee80:


    nar "Strangely, though, I can see Arnie perfectly.{w} Maybe it's her white clothing, decorated with gold."


translate English day6_ar_043b2118:


    nar "Or maybe it's her long black hair, hanging loose."


translate English day6_ar_4bf03fd5:


    nar "Quite a few of the women back home had grown their hair out to a similar length."


translate English day6_ar_2bf54be7:


    nar "When the summer brought its sticky dampness, it would really mess with their long hair, so they'd tie it up or back to keep it out of the way."


translate English day6_ar_4fa0291c:


    nar "Would the day ever come where she felt uncomfortable enough to put up her long hair?{w} The sun is always up, and yet summers in the capital are cold."


translate English day6_ar_c2ae66c6:


    nar "Were there ever days where having to manage that long hair distressed her?{w} Summers in the capital are cold, and during the polar night like this, the sun is never even out."


translate English day6_ar_7d2bc690:


    nar "I remember how dark the skies had been when I'd just arrived.{w} I've never felt warmth here in the capital."


translate English day6_ar_c17d4ee9:


    nar "So I have no idea what it's been like for her over the years during the warmer season."


translate English day6_ar_bcebf5d9:


    nar "I look up to the ceiling and see light there.{w} The same light that had shone at her back the day we first met."


translate English day6_ar_846ab0ea:


    nar "It looks like the sun, but I know it's man-made."


translate English day6_ar_11f2c1b4:


    nar "The temperature is pleasant; I can't even feel heat.{w} I want to show her the real sun."


translate English day6_ar_10fbd3a9:


    nar "I can't imagine Arnie struggling under the sun's heat, but she'd probably tie her hair back like the ladies who were fine with it."


translate English day6_ar_e849823b:


    nar "She'd probably stand there in childlike wonder, feeling the heat on her skin for the first time."


translate English day6_ar_2ab1b6e6:


    nar "We'd run around looking for shade, and when our faces were so sweaty it looked like we'd been rained on, we'd wipe them off and have some nice, cold water together."


translate English day6_ar_e7b010b7:


    nar "That, alone, would be so much fun. And yet..."


translate English day6_ar_d85dc1ad:


    nar "BAM!!!{w} A sharp palm noise cuts through my reverie, causing my eyes to flash open."


translate English day6_ar_57564f16:


    nar "Apparently I'd dozed off."


translate English day6_ar_908436da:


    ar "Brother?"


translate English day6_ar_27721515:


    nar "With the world still unfocused and blurry, she talks to me."


translate English day6_ar_2d24e1a6:


    nar "Compared to the dream I had, the way she stands against the artificial light makes her seem so much darker."


translate English day6_ar_a34f4df8:


    pl "Yaaawn... Are you done?"


translate English day6_ar_27825a29:


    ar "Yes. I'm terribly sorry to have made you wait like this.{w} You seem tired. Are you feeling well?"


translate English day6_ar_0f3b622d:


    pl "Yeah, I'm fine. Just a little drowsy, I guess."


translate English day6_ar_088f44fc:


    nar "I brush back my hair and look around, but nobody else is here."


translate English day6_ar_948f4928:


    nar "No more voices echo in the training grounds, which now feel too big for just the two of us."


translate English day6_ar_a28b9780:


    pl "Did the other priests head off to work?"


translate English day6_ar_ba0a593e:


    ar "Admirably, yes."


translate English day6_ar_6f52889a:


    pl "I feel kinda bad...{w} Are you sure you don't have to go to work? I could just get my clothes later."


translate English day6_ar_0f4ff83d:


    ar "There is something I wish to tell you today, no matter what else happens.{w} And I've received the time to do so."


translate English day6_ar_453d665b:


    pl "Wait... What did you want to tell me?"


translate English day6_ar_6d5078ab:


    ar "Well, it's... It's something very important to me."


translate English day6_ar_3261b4d3:


    pl "...Alright, I guess."


translate English day6_ar_53a3199c:


    nar "I get myself back to my feet, standing in front of her.{w} I can still see the dream flitting here and there before my eyes."


translate English day6_ar_21214612:


    ar "This building belongs to the Magic Department.{w} While we use the first floor as a training room, the second floor is where our dormitories are."


translate English day6_ar_dbf67035:


    ar "Would you come up there with me so that I can return your clothing to you?"


translate English day6_ar_774c30b0:


    pl "That's...the first I'm hearing of it.{w} The ceiling's so high up I thought there weren't any more floors."


translate English day6_ar_50cc1345:


    ar "The building is set up in a rather peculiar way."


translate English day6_ar_2a950b89:


    pl "Are you sure an outsider like me should be up there?"


translate English day6_ar_7450d478:


    ar "You are not an outsider. You are my Brother."


translate English day6_ar_324c445c:


    pl "I guess, if you insist..."


translate English day6_ar_30034b9d:


    nar "A heavy air settles down on my shoulders, one I've felt in the past."


translate English day6_ar_9b301e86:


    nar "It's calm here, but there's a scent in the air--one that's so calm it's actually kind of irritating."


translate English day6_ar_103b2481:


    nar "From the gorgeous, darkly-colored wallpaper to the golden decorations all about, you can tell this is the Magic Department's building at a glance."


translate English day6_ar_83c3c04e:


    pl "Hey, do you guys burn a specific kind of incense like the Academics Department or something?{w} I smelled something like this when I went to their place..."


translate English day6_ar_40441d35:


    ar "No, we do not burn any scents in particular.{w} If there is a peculiar smell about, then that would be the wood."


translate English day6_ar_10c2cbc5:


    ar "The walls and floors are all constructed of wood; it's a peculiarity of my uncle's."


translate English day6_ar_e911e332:


    pl "Really? So this is what expensive wood smells like, huh?"


translate English day6_ar_4022541c:


    ar "Does it displease you somehow?"


translate English day6_ar_0ae67326:


    pl "Nah, just the opposite.{w} The Cleanup Department's dorms always have a smoky odor because of all the mold."


translate English day6_ar_483c5328:


    pl "I bet you've never seen mold, though, Arnie."


translate English day6_ar_374b2e6c:


    ar "I cannot refute that...{w} As this is the place you will be using soon, I believe it would be best to remember the path we took."


translate English day6_ar_dd5459dc:


    pl "Right... Guess so."


translate English day6_ar_506bcbf3:


    nar "I remembered what I forgot.{w} Tomorrow will be one week, marking when I'll be leaving the Cleanup Department."


translate English day6_ar_4e042a29:


    nar "I expected that to be refreshing, but for some reason, it's not."


translate English day6_ar_61e6684b:


    nar "There's a bunch of reasons for it, but I guess the biggest one is because of her."


translate English day6_ar_f8203e79:


    nar "Our engagement never felt real at first, almost like it was happening to someone else.{w} At this point, though, it feels much more real."


translate English day6_ar_fbf525f2:


    nar "To be honest, I haven't seriously thought about it yet."


translate English day6_ar_7b27098b:


    nar "They all have such earnest attitudes that at some point, I started trying to escape reality."


translate English day6_ar_ac473c90:


    ar "Please enter."


translate English day6_ar_951c7cc1:


    nar "I stand there in front of the opened door for a few moments, unable to parse what's happening.{w} My eyes dart between the room and Arnie."


translate English day6_ar_14bfcfa2:


    pl "Please enter?"


translate English day6_ar_10c02e3a:


    ar "Yes. This is a single-person room, so I cannot deny it's rather cramped, but..."


translate English day6_ar_31ba0747:


    pl "That's not exactly what I meant..."


translate English day6_ar_117ae52f:


    ar "Is there some other problem, then?"


translate English day6_ar_7bf56674:


    nar "She looks at me in confusion, and I stare back in silence.{w} I start to feel stupid for worrying like that."


translate English day6_ar_27f81f9c:


    nar "Getting married to someone like this? I wonder if she's had the chance to seriously think this through. I just don't get it anymore."


translate English day6_ar_5fc0e9af:


    pl "No, I'll go in..."


translate English day6_ar_c214b6ad:


    ar "You can feel free to relax in here."


translate English day6_ar_62a6690a:


    nar "My first time inside Arnie's room reveals nothing particularly beautiful or special."


translate English day6_ar_90c45b3a:


    nar "It's so much larger than the cramped, suffocating rooms in the Cleanup Department."


translate English day6_ar_4ffd7258:


    nar "Each piece of furniture is very classy, but I can't shake the feeling that it's all stereotypical."


translate English day6_ar_e4822e4a:


    nar "It smells about the same in here, too.{w} The other rooms are likely no different. That gives me a faint sense of relief."


translate English day6_ar_0bdca666:


    ar "I'm terribly sorry for their being no chairs, but you may feel free to sit anywhere you like."


translate English day6_ar_6154acff:


    pl "It's really clean in here, so we can sit on the floor just fine.{w} Very like you to have clean floors, Arnie."


translate English day6_ar_4861ecbe:


    ar "I am honored you feel that way."


translate English day6_ar_add8b4fc:


    nar "As I took another long look around, I spotted something I didn't see when I first came in."


translate English day6_ar_797a980f:


    nar "On the chest of drawers next to the bed is a flower vase."


translate English day6_ar_17e944ab:


    nar "It doesn't look like anything special, but it seems to clash slightly with the calm, dimly lit room."


translate English day6_ar_f45334bc:


    pl "Did you put those flowers in?"


translate English day6_ar_d0f28536:


    ar "Flowers... Ah, you mean the vase on the dresser?"


translate English day6_ar_b5fb5979:


    pl "Yeah. They don't seem like they came with the room."


translate English day6_ar_e909c43f:


    ar "Those flowers were a little gift I received from my uncle."


translate English day6_ar_ad878658:


    ar "He gave them to me as a commemoration when I received the blessing of being an auxiliary bishop."


translate English day6_ar_b5ae5004:


    pl "The Magic Department bishop? He gave them to you?"


translate English day6_ar_6b5d6a80:


    ar "Yes, though it's been several years since then."


translate English day6_ar_230083c2:


    pl "I just can't picture that.{w} He really loves you, huh?"


translate English day6_ar_80e7baf4:


    ar "It's rather embarrassing.{w} Others may view it as a show of partiality."


translate English day6_ar_e452e296:


    ar "But he loves his family deeply and is very empathetic.{w} He is always thinking about what would be best for the priests in his department and for the temple as a whole."


translate English day6_ar_1107bf3c:


    ar "Still, his inability to properly express himself in certain situations is rather troubling."


translate English day6_ar_0ca32818:


    pl "Troubling, huh..."


translate English day6_ar_ec68b225:


    ar "He worries quite a lot about your safety as well, Brother.{w} He gives me a reminder of it every day."


translate English day6_ar_a946ab1e:


    pl "He told me to get along with you too, and be better friends or whatever."


translate English day6_ar_734acfc6:


    ar "Hee hee.{w} That is very like my uncle."


translate English day6_ar_2f73b925:


    pl "I would have gotten along with you even if the bishop hadn't said anything."


translate English day6_ar_aea18a95:


    ar "I would have as well."


translate English day6_ar_5d478e85:


    nar "I really want to ask whether that's true."


translate English day6_ar_404a588b:


    nar "Would she actually have treated me with such kindness even if the bishop didn't have anything to do with me?"


translate English day6_ar_d44bfed6:


    nar "But I'm still too scared to ask her that."


translate English day6_ar_37c1cc1b:


    ar "I've brought your clothes.{w} If you would, please check them over to make sure there are no issues."


translate English day6_ar_2b70f71e:


    pl "Don't really see any, so thanks."


translate English day6_ar_ffa63a2d:


    nar "After taking the heavy, belt-laden vestments from her, I feel myself flush with embarrassment as I remember what happened yesterday."


translate English day6_ar_0a464cc4:


    pl "Hey, uh... I'm really sorry about yesterday."


translate English day6_ar_720d9619:


    ar "What are you apologizing about?"


translate English day6_ar_fd94cd7f:


    pl "I kinda ran off all of a sudden in front of the bishop, and your clothes got dirty because of me.{w} Sorry about that. I haven't been feeling great lately..."


translate English day6_ar_ac729b9f:


    ar "All actions have reasons behind them.{w} There is nothing you must apologize for."


translate English day6_ar_f218222d:


    pl "But--"


translate English day6_ar_570eda3c:


    ar "You know, when we first met, I thought you were a bolder man, one confident in all his actions."


translate English day6_ar_a9023d40:


    ar "But you've seemed constantly down as of late."


translate English day6_ar_90afc18d:


    pl "Do you want to know why?{w} It's because of how great you are."


translate English day6_ar_664a2257:


    ar "How great I am...?"


translate English day6_ar_f8f5c588:


    pl "Yeah. Any guy would probably go weak in the knees with you in front of them."


translate English day6_ar_f9190f88:


    ar "Ah. I shall take that as a compliment as well."


translate English day6_ar_146820ec:


    nar "I'm not kidding around.{w} When I'm with her, I feel pathetic."


translate English day6_ar_0c4cb6aa:


    nar "I doubt I would have ever felt like this if I'd met her as a complete stranger, too."


translate English day6_ar_9a3534e5:


    ar "I must apologize for surprising you with what we talked about yesterday."


translate English day6_ar_1e9bd8f6:


    ar "I had thought I needed some time to really talk things out, but my uncle beat me to the punch, as it were."


translate English day6_ar_af1607e0:


    pl "Oh.{w} Yeah, that sure shocked me!"


translate English day6_ar_f4768282:


    pl "I couldn't believe he'd say that stuff in front of you!{w} Did he not care that you were there?"


translate English day6_ar_5e429d70:


    ar "He only stated the facts that have been public since I was very young."


translate English day6_ar_d7fa2a0e:


    ar "In the same way, my uncle only wished to give you the truth.{w} There's nothing wrong with that."


translate English day6_ar_3f5b75c4:


    pl "Nothing wrong with that?{w} Aren't you scared that you might die young?"


translate English day6_ar_ccffb290:


    ar "The divine revelation passed down from ancient times states that the eldest child of the Alternatas will have an especially short lifespan."


translate English day6_ar_79b5ebe8:


    ar "Should that happen to me, then God will have only been following the fate He himself decreed."


translate English day6_ar_14e08ea3:


    ar "In fact, it will allow me to prove that I lack nothing as the eldest Alternata child.{w} I haven't a single worry about it."


translate English day6_ar_1680c80e:


    pl "I mean, you've gotta respect the optimism.{w} It's just that I don't have as much faith as you, so it scares me."


translate English day6_ar_38d00e5b:


    pl "I think Enoch feels the same way--and the bishop probably does, too."


translate English day6_ar_d3264252:


    ar "I'm well aware of their concerns.{w} Their sound walls of good intentions protect me to this very day."


translate English day6_ar_4b767b74:


    ar "I'm always thankful and honored that I'm able to receive all that goodwill."


translate English day6_ar_c6a353e8:


    ar "So please, do not worry.{w} I will not be disheartened so easily."


translate English day6_ar_e28b3cf0:


    pl "Sigh...{w} Well, not like I believe some random \"divine revelation\" anyway."


translate English day6_ar_291fdff4:


    pl "But yeah--you don't seem like the kind of person who would lose heart very easily."


translate English day6_ar_c2837e1b:


    pl "What about your father?{w} Wasn't he killed by the cardinal?"


translate English day6_ar_8b67c658:


    ar "My uncle assumes as much, yes. He has been searching for evidence for a long time now."


translate English day6_ar_4738f699:


    ar "But to tell you the truth, I don't feel there is any need to seek out his cause of death."


translate English day6_ar_5efb56bd:


    pl "...Really?"


translate English day6_ar_03132b96:


    ar "Yes. My father passed away when I was just learning to read and write."


translate English day6_ar_d235d55c:


    ar "But I can still remember his face and his voice vividly.{w} He was a very kind man."


translate English day6_ar_5ec44e4c:


    ar "He treated me like he would have treated a normal child, despite knowing of all the burdens on my shoulders."


translate English day6_ar_f5a36d13:


    ar "And while he lived, he would frequently take me to see the outside world."


translate English day6_ar_c35eb648:


    ar "Hee hee...{w} He loved birds very much."


translate English day6_ar_89778a91:


    ar "Sometimes he would complain to me that he wished he could just drop everything and listen to their voices outside for the entire day."


translate English day6_ar_a6550c3e:


    pl "If you loved your father that much, then why don't you want to investigate...?"


translate English day6_ar_ee03bbae:


    ar "My father taught me a great many things.{w} One of those things related to life and fate."


translate English day6_ar_dfc92382:


    ar "Fate is assigned by God at the moment of one's birth, unchangeable by mere man."


translate English day6_ar_e0783f56:


    ar "We all live in accordance with the fate we are assigned."


translate English day6_ar_ee53e77a:


    ar "But there is no reason to lament or be sad, for all our lives have meaning."


translate English day6_ar_65d4e2a0:


    ar "I was a very spoiled child back then, so I didn't understand what he meant.{w} In fact, I cried for three days and three nights."


translate English day6_ar_a8270583:


    ar "After the rains came and went, I saw the clear skies, so fair as to sober any drunkard.{w} But the weather only frustrated me more, and I cried again."


translate English day6_ar_43f95161:


    ar "Eventually, it was my uncle who pulled me from that pit."


translate English day6_ar_2369f96c:


    nar "Though her voice is almost monotone, she smiles as she talks, as though recounting a fun memory."


translate English day6_ar_40e12ec9:


    nar "There isn't a trace of the child who must have cried and cried at her father's death, his cold body lying there, pelted by the rain."


translate English day6_ar_e08f6973:


    nar "She's only lived for a couple more years than me, but whenever she talks about things like this, she feels like a full-fledged adult--and so much older than me."


translate English day6_ar_642355ff:


    nar "A year for her means something far different than a year for me."


translate English day6_ar_50ff6b49:


    ar "Now, my belief is that my father's death was part of his fate.{w} I have faith that he believed as much as well."


translate English day6_ar_2d452cc6:


    ar "That is not the part I regret.{w} What I regret, and what mortifies me, is that when my parents were breathing their last breaths, I couldn't be at their side to protect them."


translate English day6_ar_a925ec4d:


    ar "But even that shame is part of what they left me.{w} And so, I will remain an inexcusable person, always."


translate English day6_ar_8a08639c:


    pl "Woah..."


translate English day6_ar_9476cd78:


    ar "I'm sorry--I've been talking your ear off.{w} Will that suffice as an answer?"


translate English day6_ar_1856a1e0:


    pl "I think I get how you feel."


translate English day6_ar_d86e508b:


    pl "But I definitely can't understand it.{w} I mean, to be honest, I don't think there's much we can do about people dying to the Pestis, but..."


translate English day6_ar_550281ef:


    pl "I also think we should do whatever we can to stop it."


translate English day6_ar_47c08998:


    pl "Especially if unfair things happen.{w} If someone ever killed you, I don't think I'd ever be able to forgive them."


translate English day6_ar_55d08021:


    ar "I've heard that the reason people yearn for meetings is because everyone has a different way of thinking."


translate English day6_ar_8374df5a:


    ar "Perhaps the expression isn't quite apt, but I'm happy to have heard your viewpoint."


translate English day6_ar_60446a62:


    pl "I don't think I've ever seen you happier than when you talk about your family."


translate English day6_ar_cab5f27f:


    ar "Is that so?{w} I believe it's only because you are here to listen."


translate English day6_ar_60c1807c:


    ar "Words are meant to be heard by others--voices are meant to be used so others can listen."


translate English day6_ar_a255685d:


    pl "Then what about me?{w} If you had the chance to talk about me to others, would you still think that was enjoyable?"


translate English day6_ar_e3a23600:


    ar "Yes. I would enjoy it more than anything else."


translate English day6_ar_36fce75d:


    pl "How... How can you think that way?"


translate English day6_ar_ad149b50:


    ar "Because you are already as family to me."


translate English day6_ar_26c1c29f:


    pl "Isn't that only because your uncle decided that for us?"


translate English day6_ar_96c4ba14:


    nar "A moment later, the smile that's been on her face the whole time goes away.{w} But I can't take back the words. Not now that I've uttered them."


translate English day6_ar_9ac6a4be:


    pl "It is, isn't it?{w} And he only brought me here because God chose me or whatever.{w} But that's all just a coincidence."


translate English day6_ar_81b0a2f9:


    pl "If not for that revelation--if the bishop hadn't brought me in to be your fianc..."


translate English day6_ar_90debd02:


    pl "Actually, we probably would have never met at all.{w} Doesn't all of this sound stupid in that light?"


translate English day6_ar_52ebe497:


    ar "There are no coincidences in this world, Brother.{w} God chose you because--"


translate English day6_ar_8a2566de:


    pl "Yeah, yeah, fine.{w} Then let's assume it WAS fate, like you're saying.{w} I guess what's important is, how do you feel about me?"


translate English day6_ar_4e0a6719:


    pl "Haven't you ever thought about it?{w} Like, apart from your uncle getting us engaged, or from any God-given reasons."


translate English day6_ar_a7971414:


    pl "Have you ever seriously thought about me, as a person?"


translate English day6_ar_1d965c5f:


    pl "I know I'm being rude and arrogant, but I've been thinking about this stuff day in, day out. I can't help myself."


translate English day6_ar_2cd352a2:


    pl "Family duties and faith in God are all you talk about, so I have no idea what you actually think of me.{w} I get worried, you know?"


translate English day6_ar_2b33cd9a:


    pl "So worried it feels like it's gonna drive me crazy. Does that make sense?"


translate English day6_ar_f64466f1_1:


    ar "......"


translate English day6_ar_e2a110cc:


    nar "I couldn't resist saying it anymore--it's like the dam broke, and it all came pouring out.{w} As the heat fades from my head, it's replaced by a sudden fear."


translate English day6_ar_230532f6:


    nar "There's no running away anymore.{w} I can't ignore it now.{w} The time has come to confront whatever's truly in her mind."


translate English day6_ar_a1697118:


    ar "Ever since I met you...{w} Ever since I exchanged words with you, not a day has gone by that I didn't think of you."


translate English day6_ar_eb1e660c:


    pl "......"


translate English day6_ar_2dfd9447:


    nar "I open my eyes, closed tightly as they were in fear, and look at her straight in the eye."


translate English day6_ar_d88e33c2:


    nar "Unlike me, she's never averted her gaze from me--not even once."


translate English day6_ar_f95b127c:


    nar "Her gaze is direct, and I see water droplets I never would have seen normally."


translate English day6_ar_c1701c3b:


    nar "She has her hands neatly together as if offering a prayer to someone."


translate English day6_ar_44896d4f:


    ar "I'm terribly sorry.{w} I've needlessly worried you by not expressing my true feelings sooner."


translate English day6_ar_710d6b3d:


    ar "Though I am ashamed to admit it, I was afraid of what your answer would be."


translate English day6_ar_160fb5c0:


    ar "I want you to give me a true answer--the one in your heart.{w} That is why I called you here today."


translate English day6_ar_2e2925fb:


    nar "She stops, then opens her mouth again, her voice trembling through the air."


translate English day6_ar_d421ed2d:


    ar "I love you."


translate English day6_ar_25b4e1d8:


    nar "And what spills from her lips is nothing particularly special--they're simply words expressing one's love for another."


translate English day6_ar_0aa827bb:


    nar "Somewhere deep down, I must have anticipated this, because I didn't feel much emotion or shock from it."


translate English day6_ar_8a77353d:


    nar "I don't say anything right away only because my throat is parched from having talked for so long without having any water."


translate English day6_ar_1df887ac:


    ar "I, Arne Alternata, love you from the bottom of my heart."


translate English day6_ar_0a5d9a7e:


    nar "One of the organs behind my bones gives a creak."


translate English day6_ar_80fca488:


    nar "My heart hurts. It's pounding so hard it feels like it'll split open.{w} I close my eyes again, bracing against the pain."


translate English day6_ar_d5f078dd:


    nar "It's like I can see the blood rising from my heart to my brain creating images behind my eyelids."


translate English day6_ar_e5d7f989:


    nar "My fists are clenched so tightly that they're now a little sweaty.{w} It's too cool to be feeling heat like that."


translate English day6_ar_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "......"


translate English day6_ar_9cac1f4e:


    nar "She says nothing else after those words.{w} She's waiting for my answer, like she said before."


translate English day6_ar_0e06a242:


    nar "An awful silence drifts through the room, neither of us saying anything.{w} Not even the sound of the air can be heard."


translate English day6_ar_e5969c77:


    nar "My eyes dart about, looking for an escape.{w} But everything in the room is unfamiliar; there is nothing to calm me down."


translate English day6_ar_e1b04d2f:


    nar "I'm still thirsty.{w} Maybe I should have asked for a glass of water."


translate English day6_ar_3cc12125:


    nar "I feel bad for her.{w} She must have been worried about those three words for days now."


translate English day6_ar_a4d06c2e:


    nar "Considering her family environment, I doubt anyone has ever taught her how to tell someone she loves them."


translate English day6_ar_b86f6aea:


    nar "She worried about those words in her heart for days, then found the courage to say them.{w} I..."


translate English day6_ar_fe099643:


    pl "I'm sorry."


translate English day6_ar_696833a7:


    nar "I can't accept her heart's desire."


translate English day6_ar_04d54594:


    nar "The earnest devotion inside her is too heavy a responsibility for me to burden.{w} I'm not confident enough that I can stay at her side forever."


translate English day6_ar_1a8c56fd:


    nar "After all, there's already a girl that I like."


translate English day6_ar_8ef9f2dc:


    nar "A girl...that I like..."


translate English day6_ar_e6edecbb:


    nar "I wracked my brain every which way, but in the end, that one simple word was what came out of my mouth."


translate English day6_ar_aece7614:


    ar "...Ah, I see."


translate English day6_ar_d08efce0:


    nar "She smiles lightly and calmly, without a hint of any lost love visible in her expression."


translate English day6_ar_02570bd0:


    nar "The tears are no longer in her moist eyes.{w} She undoes her hands."


translate English day6_ar_6f85091b:


    nar "She places one of her hands on her chest; she can probably feel her heartbeat through it."


translate English day6_ar_e82d250f:


    nar "She lets out several breaths, like newborn breathing, then takes in several new ones."


translate English day6_ar_94fdb1de:


    ar "Thank you for telling me your true feelings.{w} I'm very happy you were the one who let me feel this emotion for the first time in my life."


translate English day6_ar_f6c97f41:


    nar "The moment I see that smile, the corners of my eyes heat up for some reason.{w} This time, the warm emotions pressing against me burst out in the form of tears."


translate English day6_ar_c7747eda:


    nar "I sniffled, crying, unable to hide my mistrust of my own emotions until wiping those tears dry."


translate English day6_ar_3607487a:


    nar "Ashamed, I choke everything back, closing off my parched throat.{w} The sound stops.{w} But when I notice it stop, the tears flow again."


translate English day6_ar_f64466f1_2:


    ar "......"


translate English day6_ar_7cf0ecb7:


    nar "She always places a hand on my shoulder and comforts me in these situations, but I can't raise my deeply bowed head enough to care."


translate English day6_ar_ebd09186:


    nar "I wonder what kind of face she's making.{w} Is she regretting having had feelings for me at all, now that she's seeing me in such an awful state?"


translate English day6_ar_daf8e9e8:


    nar "That day, I spurned her.{w} And yet my own crying was the only thing to be heard in the tranquil room."


translate English day6_rs_28e52210:


    br "\n I'm pretty sure I've observed her for a while now, but I haven't learned anything about her by doing so. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_rs_8ac1e264:


    extend "\n If it was possible, I'd pry open her little head and see what was inside. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_rs_8e92a9e2:


    extend "\n But the longer I think about that, the more ridiculous an idea it seems. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_rs_8280a172:


    extend "\n So here's my thought.{w} Her lack of understanding means the books she's read up until now have fallen out of her mind."


translate English day6_rs_d7a1d99d:



    nvl clear
    br "\n But what about her totally round belly? I'm sure the books she's devoured in the past are still in there. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_rs_9b24c65f:


    extend "\n Because not \"digesting\" a book's contents means it stays in the stomach. She must have stopped being able to move around with all that weight. {w}{nw}"


translate English day6_rs_984c1667:


    extend "\n These are basically the ideas I've been having.{w} And it's because I've been reading too many children's stories in that surreal place with a girl who barely seems human."


translate English day6_rs_76b2fe88:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_rs_76b2fe88_1:


    nvl clear


translate English day6_rs_428aadce:


    nar "The library is quiet as always.{w} I open the unlocked door and enter Rose's room and see her curled up, asleep."


translate English day6_rs_dd34014f:


    nar "But she seems somehow different from usual.{w} There's books scattered all around her; they're usually neatly tucked away on the shelf."


translate English day6_rs_24ee774d:


    nar "And they're all children's books as well--ones from the fourth shelf from the top that she always talks about.{w} When did she have time to read this many?"


translate English day6_rs_78662478:


    nar "Something's definitely up."


translate English day6_rs_2abc3d65:


    nar "Maybe it's just because the mood in the library is always so heavy, and because they keep so many books, but I can't sense an ounce of unnecessary moisture or heat. It was always the same in this room."


translate English day6_rs_67faacb9:


    nar "But not today. Now, it's almost physically suffocating.{w} With this library underground, there are no windows, and thus no breezes can get in."


translate English day6_rs_5f683548:


    nar "How long has the indoor air here been settling and sinking?"


translate English day6_rs_eb1e660c:


    pl "......"


translate English day6_rs_c517e7d0:


    nar "She doesn't move an inch in her slumber."


translate English day6_rs_28c2c864:


    nar "Her eyes are shut, her little body all curled up, as though she'd found a shadowy place she'd been desperately seeking. I can't even hear her breathing."


translate English day6_rs_bfb9373c:


    nar "Almost like she's never been anything but a stuffed wax doll."


translate English day6_rs_eb671636:


    nar "Unbreathing, unspeaking, unliving--a mere doll."


translate English day6_rs_da3a6a0e:


    pl "Rose?"


translate English day6_rs_c7016bbf:


    nar "I softly call her name.{w} She doesn't answer."


translate English day6_rs_e130fd9f:


    nar "Looking at her from up close, I get the impression that if she was a doll, she wasn't very well-made."


translate English day6_rs_8c3ddc28:


    nar "Her forehead protrudes and her eyebrows are uneven. Her eyes are awfully far apart, too."


translate English day6_rs_68328c5f:


    nar "Hidden behind her scraggly bangs, her eyes show no sign of opening. Every so often, they'll twitch in response to my breaths."


translate English day6_rs_5590e007:


    nar "Round cheeks atop a short neck. I can't usually see her pale neck, since it's usually behind her collar, but I see a droplet on it."


translate English day6_rs_a0ee15cd:


    nar "It's sweat.{w} The stuffy, sticky heat reminds me all too well of summer, a season I haven't thought about for a while."


translate English day6_rs_5445870e:


    nar "As soon as I notice it, I grab her round nose between my thumb and forefinger."


translate English day6_rs_65cee16f:


    nar "Her smooth little nose doesn't react much at first, but it quickly begins to twitch as less and less air passes through it."


translate English day6_rs_003bf2e4:


    rs "Mrnn..."


translate English day6_rs_2ffd1821:


    nar "With a popping of escaping air, I let go of her nose."


translate English day6_rs_94ce8808:


    nar "There's a little moisture on my hand.{w} She stirs for a few moments, then opens her clouded eyes, finally looking up through her sweeping bangs at me."


translate English day6_rs_1d9e4b19:


    pl "Rose! You're alive!"


translate English day6_rs_8f1693b6:


    nar "That was probably the strangest interjection I could have come up with."


translate English day6_rs_79358937:


    nar "Rose still seems half asleep. She doesn't rub her eyes or get up; she just stares at me."


translate English day6_rs_9113ddf4:


    nar "Giving up on our staring contest, I grab her skinny shoulders and shake her."


translate English day6_rs_bf15721d:


    pl "C'mon, wake up. We're going outside."


translate English day6_rs_ad3e213b:


    rs "Outside...?"


translate English day6_rs_870076ec:


    pl "Yep. You don't get much fresh air here."


translate English day6_rs_2955ec4d:


    nar "Then, suddenly, Rose shakes her head."


translate English day6_rs_30bc8b65:


    nar "She pulls away--firmly, too, enough that it hurts my arms."


translate English day6_rs_8ac478f1:


    rs "This is Rose's place. This is where Rose is allowed to be.{w} I'm not supposed to leave."


translate English day6_rs_35d91a5a:


    pl "I don't get it. Stop being stubborn. You're sweating."


translate English day6_rs_16dde463:


    rs "I mustn't leave. I mustn't leave...!"


translate English day6_rs_3cd80ec2:


    nar "Having reaffirmed my grip on her shoulders, I quickly let go, then grab her cheeks as they go side to side with her head shaking instead."


translate English day6_rs_29a963f1:


    pl "Rose! You're the only one who thinks that.{w} You're allowed to leave!"


translate English day6_rs_dd653cb0:


    nar "Rose stops. Her wide eyes blink."


translate English day6_rs_9a4f537f:


    rs "Rose is the only one...?"


translate English day6_rs_d3de1495:


    pl "Yeah. Nobody ordered you to stay in here no matter what."


translate English day6_rs_1c31135a:


    pl "And even if someone did, you could blame me for it anyway. Get it?"


translate English day6_rs_3ecdee97:


    rs "......"


translate English day6_rs_e45c9528:


    nar "Rose relaxes.{w} Seizing the opportunity, I bring her outside."


translate English day6_rs_20eb872c:


    nar "The air in the library is still dry and comfortable--it feels like a totally different space than that room."


translate English day6_rs_65eebe36:


    nar "Rose stares as if in a daze back at the door, which is still open."


translate English day6_rs_06198c87:


    pl "Phew. It was so hot in there I thought I was gonna die...{w} Did something happen in there? It always felt normal up until today."


translate English day6_rs_3ecdee97_1:


    rs "......"


translate English day6_rs_c2274541:


    pl "Why'd you pull out all those books?{w} You didn't... You didn't pass out from the heat reading them, did you?"


translate English day6_rs_a838f05a:


    pl "Sigh... And you didn't go out for air, even then. You're so dumb."


translate English day6_rs_3ecdee97_2:


    rs "......"


translate English day6_rs_dfff2fb7:


    pl "...Rose?"


translate English day6_rs_309b4eab:


    nar "Is she still drowsy?{w} Her eyes look weirdly empty. I wave a hand in front of them, and then, finally she peels her eyes away from the door to look at me."


translate English day6_rs_e16d9ccc:


    rs "...Good morning."


translate English day6_rs_2be4cd42:


    pl "Uhh...{w} Yeah. Good morning. A little late for that, though."


translate English day6_rs_37868981:


    rs "You came to visit me again."


translate English day6_rs_6de518e2:


    pl "Hmm. Well, I did promise. Are you happy I came?"


translate English day6_rs_ed04386a:


    rs "Yes."


translate English day6_rs_f56c79c7:


    nar "I'm surprised at her reply.{w} She's definitely a little different today."


translate English day6_rs_dd2d3e91:


    pl "Did something happen today?"


translate English day6_rs_0b2657bf:


    rs "Rose read books."


translate English day6_rs_25c155d9:


    pl "Yeah, I could tell. You had so many around you."


translate English day6_rs_35e66736:


    rs "That's because... Out of the twenty-eight books total, none of them were interesting."


translate English day6_rs_185afb7c:


    pl "Not even one of them?{w} I never thought you'd start talking about books being interesting or not."


translate English day6_rs_ecec5f22:


    pl "I thought you were just reading whatever you could get your hands on."


translate English day6_rs_1bb5e3e5:


    rs "Yes. For Rose, books are groupings of terms. They are objects meant for learning terms.{w} But you are different."


translate English day6_rs_a9b26ba2:


    pl "Me?"


translate English day6_rs_2d4911db:


    rs "For you, books are objects meant for learning new information.{w} They're objects meant for obtaining enjoyment. Am I wrong?"


translate English day6_rs_45f9b15c:


    pl "Hmm...{w} I guess you're right, which means... Were you looking for a book to recommend to me?"


translate English day6_rs_41ea9fcb:


    rs "Indeed."


translate English day6_rs_e9bb710f:


    pl "Sigh... I guess I did say that, but different people will have different ideas about what's interesting."


translate English day6_rs_21d223a5:


    rs "They will?{w} Then which book should Rose choose?"


translate English day6_rs_7f68375b:


    pl "Well... I'm glad you were trying to keep my interests in mind, and all."


translate English day6_rs_053f5ad4:


    pl "But you can just show me a book you think is interesting."


translate English day6_rs_50011bc0:


    rs "What makes something interesting?"


translate English day6_rs_f508d51f:


    pl "...Why are we back at square one again?"


translate English day6_rs_3644f020:


    pl "You know, something you like... Something you want to read again, or a sentence that stuck with you in particular. That means you find that interesting. Right?"


translate English day6_rs_22189a36:


    rs "Hmm..."


translate English day6_rs_e510a5ea:


    pl "Okay, then let's do it this way.{w} This is a library. It's got way more books than the fourth shelf in your room."


translate English day6_rs_d75dffc0:


    pl "Don't you think you could find a book or two here that you like?"


translate English day6_rs_dba58c26:


    rs "The only books Rose can read are the ones on the fourth shelf."


translate English day6_rs_e5b0e9cb:


    pl "Then just read ones from the fourth shelf in here."


translate English day6_rs_ace2c1e3:


    nar "I pull out a book from the fourth shelf on the bookshelf next to me and open it up."


translate English day6_rs_5950f78c:


    nar "Thanks to Rose, I can read basic letters now. But this being a library, it sure is tough to read."


translate English day6_rs_4ded33ae:


    pl "Have you ever read something like this?"


translate English day6_rs_dcb028f7:


    rs "...No."


translate English day6_rs_e41afb2b:


    pl "I'm sure if we look, there will be children's stories--just like the kind you like.{w} Want to look around together?"


translate English day6_rs_355096df:


    rs "Correction. Rose does not particularly enjoy children's--"


translate English day6_rs_d905daec:


    pl "We gotta hurry before someone comes."


translate English day6_rs_428c62e8:


    nar "Without listening to her response, I turn around and start walking. I hear hurried footsteps coming after me."


translate English day6_rs_6afddc76:


    nar "Since I come here every day, I've gotten used to the powerful, headache inducing scent--a little bit, at least."


translate English day6_rs_81b8c46d:


    nar "Today's scent is lavender, one I've experienced before.{w} Are purple flowers the only ones they can get to bloom in this library, or what?"


translate English day6_rs_436aa1e6:


    pl "When do people usually come to the library?"


translate English day6_rs_45b06f1f:


    rs "Is it morning right now?"


translate English day6_rs_0ee18a81:


    pl "Probably?"


translate English day6_rs_8fd213e5:


    rs "Then they will be here soon."


translate English day6_rs_6c0c3f17:


    pl "Really?"


translate English day6_rs_b214d4dd:


    rs "Rose doesn't ever leave."


translate English day6_rs_048d1d44:


    pl "Right... Well, we'll be fine. You're the auxiliary bishop of the Academics Department, after all."


translate English day6_rs_6601aa08:


    rs "?"


translate English day6_rs_a5361d12:


    pl "Hmm... I guess I should say Lavien Rose is, not you."


translate English day6_rs_f06721f5:


    rs "Is that so..."


translate English day6_rs_728b2c0d:


    pl "To be honest, I've gotten more used to seeing you than Lavien, since I see you so much."


translate English day6_rs_1c6b4f2a:


    rs "You have?"


translate English day6_rs_98bb55a7:


    pl "I run into Lavien every once in a while, but I've seen you basically every day this past week."


translate English day6_rs_a926a57c:


    pl "You might have forgotten, though..."


translate English day6_rs_53f03bd0:


    rs "Incorrect. Rose remembers."


translate English day6_rs_e5e13b37:


    pl "Seriously?"


translate English day6_rs_801566e4:


    rs "Today is the fifth day. It will soon be one week.{w} Rose remembers."


translate English day6_rs_f1817f4b:


    pl "Huh..."


translate English day6_rs_096eec75:


    nar "The fifth day already, huh?{w} Well, I'm glad I got her out of that room and all."


translate English day6_rs_550efaa9:


    nar "But are we just going to sit quietly and read books again? That'll be boring."


translate English day6_rs_d172e092:


    nar "Maybe I should teach her different kinds of ways to have fun besides reading."


translate English day6_rs_4d5a2caf:


    nar "I mull it over for a few moments, then eventually close the book and return it to the shelf.{w} Then I put my back to it and sit down on the cold floor."


translate English day6_rs_b21486a5:


    pl "Actually, let's not look for any books. It wouldn't be much fun."


translate English day6_rs_0c9d17b9:


    rs "In that case... Will you not read with me today?"


translate English day6_rs_3ad12936:


    pl "Nope. Not today."


translate English day6_rs_b84ab144:


    rs "Rose does not understand. Why not?"


translate English day6_rs_a85c6038:


    pl "Hey, calm down and take a seat. It's cooler down here."


translate English day6_rs_1c8934f7:


    rs "Rose requests a proper explanation. Why will you not read to Rose?"


translate English day6_rs_c8d988e7:


    pl "I just thought it would be more fun to hear your story instead of read a book written by some person we don't know."


translate English day6_rs_16d07ab5:


    rs "Rose's story?"


translate English day6_rs_617fbeca:


    pl "Yeah, it's just that I've known you for a week...{w} Well, five days. And I barely know anything about you."


translate English day6_rs_ab0fb1d4:


    pl "You seem like you're getting tired of reading, so why not try having a conversation with me instead?{w} Sounds fun, doesn't it?"


translate English day6_rs_34f16692:


    rs "..."


translate English day6_rs_5881fb40:


    nar "Rose sits down across from me.{w} Pale dust sticks to her black stockings. It's a little cramped between bookshelves for two people to sit."


translate English day6_rs_bab26518:


    rs "Rose has never spoken to another person.{w} Teach her how."


translate English day6_rs_1719a713:


    pl "Don't think I've ever had someone tell me to teach them how to talk to someone..."


translate English day6_rs_72a66fe5:


    pl "Anyway, let's start with you answering some of my questions. You do that normally, right?"


translate English day6_rs_9a0d57cc:


    rs "Affirmative."


translate English day6_rs_78622834:


    pl "You can just say, like, \"yeah\" or \"not really.\""


translate English day6_rs_058653a8:


    rs "Yeah."


translate English day6_rs_795dac67:


    pl "Exactly! Okay, first question...{w} Where did you live before coming to the temple?"


translate English day6_rs_9c9dbeb2:


    rs "At home."


translate English day6_rs_b5530c40:


    pl "Uh, I mean, I know that... What I'm asking is, what kind of things did you see, and what sort of people were you with?"


translate English day6_rs_f4fb8ab5:


    rs "Rose's home was in Waste District 1."


translate English day6_rs_1d87614e:


    pl "Waste District? What's that?"


translate English day6_rs_c7a8079d:


    rs "A waste district is a region where contaminants, Pestis remains, and the dregs of corpses filter out of the capital."


translate English day6_rs_c59a700f:


    rs "The water and air quality are poor, but you can buy a house there for a very cheap price. Many live there, contributing to an active economy."


translate English day6_rs_794af7c5:


    pl "The slums, in other words... I guess that's something a huge city like the capital would have, huh?"


translate English day6_rs_8c70ff6d:


    rs "In the morning, Rose purchases two jugs of milk.{w} She does not purchase a newspaper. Once a week, on Thursdays."


translate English day6_rs_9f2c2386:


    rs "She purchases necessary ingredients. She purchases three apples."


translate English day6_rs_efab5983:


    rs "She purchases two carrots.{w} She purchases one head of broccoli and one head of cauliflower. Cheese cannot be bought in town."


translate English day6_rs_1cbd1d8a:


    pl "Milk, carrots, broccoli, and cheese... Oh, I see. For a cream stew?"


translate English day6_rs_9ffe9d37:


    rs "Correct. The smell of cream stew is unpleasant, so Rose plugs her nose while eating it."


translate English day6_rs_a68e945a:


    pl "Just like I did before. Are the apples for a snack?"


translate English day6_rs_ef9436fd:


    rs "Rose ingests apples due to their significant health benefits. However, bugs like apples, so if Rose isn't careful, she can become sick to her stomach."


translate English day6_rs_60ea67f8:


    pl "That's cool. What did you do aside from eat?"


translate English day6_rs_a5cbc265:


    rs "Rose gets sufficient sleep."


translate English day6_rs_0e76d5ac:


    pl "Yeah, but I'm sure you did more than sleep, right?"


translate English day6_rs_5ab4fadb:


    rs "Rose never leaves."


translate English day6_rs_11d2fb58:


    pl "Wait a sec... Do you stay cooped up in that room because you ALWAYS have?"


translate English day6_rs_5ab4fadb_1:


    rs "Rose never leaves."


translate English day6_rs_c9849315:


    pl "Is there any other reason?"


translate English day6_rs_2bd79ad4:


    rs "A reason...? Affirmative. Rose is not permitted to leave."


translate English day6_rs_e2549ead:


    pl "Who said that?"


translate English day6_rs_773db304:


    rs "Nobody said that. Rose thought of it on her own."


translate English day6_rs_f610bf64:


    pl "Why?"


translate English day6_rs_01fef6ed:


    rs "Why what?"


translate English day6_rs_5e64e37c:


    pl "Okay, so nobody told you, right? And you thought that for a deeper reason, right?{w} Did you not like going outside? Or is it because you're frail?"


translate English day6_rs_ccca4237:


    rs "When Rose leaves, it causes sadness."


translate English day6_rs_d6a3b9ad:


    pl "To who?"


translate English day6_rs_8fd748a4:


    rs "To Lavien."


translate English day6_rs_a77ff94b:


    pl "Umm...{w} So, well... In other words...{w} What do you mean?"


translate English day6_rs_a7b90761:


    rs "Rose must not make her sad. That's why Rose stays at home."


translate English day6_rs_f104ae20:


    pl "Something... happened when you went outside, didn't it?"


translate English day6_rs_7e8ad0c2:


    rs "Rose was playing with friends."


translate English day6_rs_6bdba090:


    pl "Friends? You had friends too, then?"


translate English day6_rs_90d00a8a:


    rs "There were children in town within three years of Rose.{w} Rose watched them. They were stacking stones into a high pile."


translate English day6_rs_78580d29:


    rs "They were looking for glass shards in the sand. They were blowing air into frog's stomachs. They were playing tag while blindfolded."


translate English day6_rs_5676bedf:


    rs "Rose watched them.{w} They spoke to Rose, and we became friends."


translate English day6_rs_e123f938:


    pl "Huh... That must have been fun."


translate English day6_rs_5654bf06:


    rs "That is fun? Do you like that sort of activity?"


translate English day6_rs_13c4dc56:


    pl "I mean... I've always liked running around outside."


translate English day6_rs_8634c089:


    pl "There was nobody my age back home, so I mostly just walked around by myself or played with the little kids."


translate English day6_rs_ccfbcf2e:


    rs "Rose enjoys walking around too."


translate English day6_rs_6bd5e47b:


    pl "Really? Then it must be hard being in that room every day."


translate English day6_rs_5cbff97a:


    nar "Rose stands back up and stretches her legs.{w} I cough a little at the dust getting brushed into my face."


translate English day6_rs_d4bb921d:


    nar "All I can see is that white dust on her knees, calves, and rear end."


translate English day6_rs_4f020a8d:


    pl "Do you want to take a walk?"


translate English day6_rs_ddf74bf6:


    nar "Standing stock still, she turns only her head.{w} Looking up at the short girl is a new experience."


translate English day6_rs_362cf0e5:


    nar "I can't make out her expression because of the shadow hanging over her face, but I can tell anyway.{w} She has no expression on her face."


translate English day6_rs_f9c1dc28:


    pl "You're so sudden about stuff."


translate English day6_rs_73b3bd19:


    nar "I get up too, then shake off my clothes.{w} I thought this while we were sitting, but it's really cramped in here with the two of us next to each other."


translate English day6_rs_70cda080:


    nar "Looking down at Rose again, I see her usual, slow blinking."


translate English day6_rs_c2acbb64:


    pl "Your clothes are dirty. Dust them off."


translate English day6_rs_bc6aca92:


    nar "Rose must not know what that phrase meant."


translate English day6_rs_7823e56b:


    nar "Because she keeps grabbing her hem and slowly turning it up and down, seeming to get confused."


translate English day6_rs_ae34b2c3:


    nar "I wish I someone else could have seen this."


translate English day6_rs_3c61ba7b:


    pl "You dummy. Do it like me."


translate English day6_rs_97416ba0:


    nar "I brush off the dust on me, exaggerating the motions to serve as an example. She's just like a little kid at this point."


translate English day6_rs_31b3a74d:


    rs "Like this?"


translate English day6_rs_612323e8:


    pl "Yeah, that was good."


translate English day6_rs_a739372e:


    rs "Phew."


translate English day6_rs_be01a209:


    pl "How did you like talking to someone?"


translate English day6_rs_70bd824b:


    nar "Her wide eyes go left and right, as though she needs to think about the answer."


translate English day6_rs_b5faa002:


    rs "Did you like it?"


translate English day6_rs_8fc3e7e5:


    pl "Did I never tell you not to answer a question with another question?{w} Well, the answer's yes. I had fun. I got to learn a little bit about you."


translate English day6_rs_14b8c72e:


    rs "Then Rose had fun as well."


translate English day6_rs_38df71ea:


    pl "You should talk to people more. Stories don't mean much if there's nobody to listen to them."


translate English day6_rs_058653a8_1:


    rs "Yeah."


translate English day6_rs_46a3ad57:


    pl "You're getting better at replying."


translate English day6_rs_10fd3391:


    nar "Whether it's because of the reply or for some other reason, Rose suddenly gets on her tiptoes and peers into my face."


translate English day6_rs_e88625d5:


    rs "Will you read a book?"


translate English day6_rs_6cc263fa:


    pl "N-Now?!"


translate English day6_rs_2327bcde:


    rs "Will you not read one? Will you?"


translate English day6_rs_0bc78056:


    pl "Are we done talking, then?"


translate English day6_rs_e9e3ad0c:


    rs "Will you not read one?"


translate English day6_rs_ffd12377:


    nar "I honestly figured that if I did things this way, she'd be focused on listening to me all day...{w} Apparently, it wasn't that easy."


translate English day6_rs_85dbdcf9:


    pl "If you want me to read a book, then I can read one."


translate English day6_rs_30e99d3e:


    rs "You'll read one?"


translate English day6_rs_fa35b96a:


    pl "But in exchange, you have to choose the book. Make it one you like."


translate English day6_rs_15671608:


    rs "Choose one book Rose likes..."


translate English day6_rs_bc1aa340:


    pl "You remember what that means, right? I just explained it."


translate English day6_rs_ea66a0bb:


    nar "She goes up to the shelves, her head poking this way and that, her hands occasionally moving."


translate English day6_rs_029edb73:


    nar "She seems to be hesitant to touch any of the books. I pull one off the fourth shelf too."


translate English day6_rs_272e0737:


    nar "Rose stops and stares at me.{w} I don't think this book has a story in it either."


translate English day6_rs_49592614:


    nar "This is the Academics Department library, so I guess most of these are dictionaries or reference books or whatever."


translate English day6_rs_b49ac29e:


    nar "I hear an odd rustling.{w} As I look away from the books, I see something that's just as odd as the sound."


translate English day6_rs_9265d1d8:


    nar "As soon as she took the book I gave her, she put it back in between two other books, and then they all fell to the floor."


translate English day6_rs_9c84f92f:


    nar "The neatly packed-in books fall in threes or fours at a time."


translate English day6_rs_07f4f3e9:


    nar "She purposely uses her hands every time a thick book falls to her, letting me know that her actions were not a simple mistake."


translate English day6_rs_dcbfbad5:


    nar "In the blink of an eye, the many books embroidering the floor get so mixed up that you can't tell what order they were originally in, forming a mere pile of paper."


translate English day6_rs_f8e1e87d:


    pl "Whoa..."


translate English day6_rs_f04315c3:


    nar "The pile of books filling the floor is oddly surreal, giving rise to that interjection for a moment."


translate English day6_rs_f7c4217d:


    nar "The shelf, now with a whole row of books taken out, looks like a little kid with missing teeth."


translate English day6_rs_39a30899:


    nar "Rose stands there blankly, watching me rather than the books."


translate English day6_rs_03cef29f:


    nar "We gaze at each other as though nothing happened."


translate English day6_rs_dcfc73ec:


    pl "What was that?"


translate English day6_rs_dd2e1fd1:


    nar "It's rather terrifying to see all the books, once neatly arranged, around her dirty shoes, and that sense of the situation drags me back to reality."


translate English day6_rs_189ce42d:


    nar "But Rose keeps her mouth shut, saying nothing, as though still inside that bubble of unreality."


translate English day6_rs_aeb23be7:


    pl "I said, what was that? What are you going to do with all these?"


translate English day6_rs_0929b8a8:


    rs "You don't like this?"


translate English day6_rs_3386306e:


    pl "...Why would I like it? It's a total mess."


translate English day6_rs_52b770e0:


    nar "Suddenly, I recall the sight I first saw.{w} The books scattered about, all open."


translate English day6_rs_47da1cca:


    nar "There's definitely more books now, but the impression is the same as before.{w} Was she trying to choose a book?"


translate English day6_rs_6469710f:


    nar "After thinking that far, I pick up the fallen books, one at a time."


translate English day6_rs_d3a9f9df:


    pl "We can't just leave them like this. The library is for everyone to use."


translate English day6_rs_3ecdee97_3:


    rs "......"


translate English day6_rs_2a0511d7:


    pl "Don't just stand there and watch. Pick some up.{w} Put them back where they belong, okay?"


translate English day6_rs_e81e68f0:


    rs "What about our books?"


translate English day6_rs_33b38778:


    pl "I'll pick one out for you after. Let's just put them away for now."


translate English day6_rs_058653a8_2:


    rs "Understood."


translate English day6_rs_9b43e7c2:


    nar "As we're stuffing the books back in, heedless of their original ordering, we hear footsteps from outside."


translate English day6_rs_14160308:


    nar "Probably one person, walking leisurely on shoes that don't have very high heels."


translate English day6_rs_94c562af:


    nar "Starting to panic, I look at the books I've picked up. Then I end up grabbing Rose's bony arm and pushing her behind the bookshelf."


translate English day6_rs_435aae24:


    nar "A book gets caught under her foot, making that classic rumply paper sound."


translate English day6_rs_eb1e660c_1:


    pl "......"


translate English day6_rs_904053c1:


    nar "As the footsteps get closer, I start to get scared, so I cover Rose's mouth."


translate English day6_rs_87912fec:


    nar "When I raise my head and focus on peering behind the bookshelf, I can't tell if my hand is touching her nose or her lips or what."


translate English day6_rs_40f6f767:


    nar "I open my eyes wide, then shut them, then open them again."


translate English day6_rs_f9bce348:


    nar "It's Lavien Rose.{w} With her short, shaggy, pink hair and her long-tailed vestments."


translate English day6_rs_af03a946:


    nar "She stands there with a shocked look on her face.{w} Then she gets into a tizzy, just like I did, and begins picking up books one at a time before taking a look around."


translate English day6_rs_3ab1460f:


    nar "That's when Rose, who had been quiet as a doll, starts to groan."


translate English day6_rs_697fb1a8:


    nar "As she flails to get out of my grip, I let go of her, and--leaning forward--she bursts out of our hiding place."


translate English day6_rs_fafcaa21:


    "{nw}"


translate English day6_rs_435dba03:


    rs "My brother!"


translate English day6_rs_5586add0:


    nar "The two priests with the exact same face embrace each other."


translate English day6_rs_3972ecdd:


    nar "Lavien still looks confounded, but after she sees me carefully exit from behind the bookshelf, her expression softens."


translate English day6_rs_7c048e9d:


    rv "Good day to you, Little [na]."


translate English day6_rs_47651d3c:


    nar "That's definitely Lavien Rose.{w} The strange priest of the Academics Department I always seem to run into."


translate English day6_rs_143014c4:


    pl "Lavi, you..."


translate English day6_rs_5ab49446:


    rs "[na] let Rose out."


translate English day6_rs_0fc2b176:


    rv "Yes, it certainly seems that way."


translate English day6_rs_c212f9ee:


    rv "Even if he hadn't, I was going to explain within the next day or so. I didn't think this would happen..."


translate English day6_rs_356de2c6:


    rv "You certainly do surprise me quite a bit, Little [na]."


translate English day6_rs_9de71b54:


    pl "...I always thought it was weird.{w} You're always so busy, but every time I come to the library you're sleeping away in the corner. And I can barely have a conversation with you..."


translate English day6_rs_92b7139d:


    rs "Correction. Rose was not sleeping. She was reading."


translate English day6_rs_617619ed:


    pl "See? Conversation not going well."


translate English day6_rs_d66ec0b7:


    rv "Did... Did Rose do all this?"


translate English day6_rs_e5e0e637:


    pl "Yeah. All of a sudden, too."


translate English day6_rs_af29eedb:


    rv "That must have been quite the surprise."


translate English day6_rs_b1404aa6:


    rv "I will get everything back to normal before anyone else comes, so please don't worry about it."


translate English day6_rs_49e4c019:


    pl "Does this kind of thing happen a lot?"


translate English day6_rs_daabe762:


    rv "Well, let's not stand here talking. Why don't we go back inside first?"


translate English day6_rs_cf94e565:


    nar "The room is more comfortable now, with the door having been left open."


translate English day6_rs_194b01c7:


    nar "The two similar people stand side by side in a place I'm starting to get accustomed to seeing every day."


translate English day6_rs_02fe89a5:


    nar "They have the exact same face and clothes--it's like there's a mirror between them. But upon closer inspection, I can make out minor differences."


translate English day6_rs_e992692e:


    nar "I'd never noticed them until I saw them standing next to each other."


translate English day6_rs_3eb3e398:


    rv "Please allow me to re-introduce myself."


translate English day6_rs_c56e9e3f:


    rv "I am Lavien, and as you know, I'm the auxiliary bishop of the Academics Department.{w} That, at least, is no lie."


translate English day6_rs_699a58ec:


    rv "My lies only involved her.{w} She is Rose, my younger twin sister."


translate English day6_rs_85646d79:


    pl "You're twins...?"


translate English day6_rs_fd24884f:


    rv "There was a bit of a problem with my official appointment as priest, you see."


translate English day6_rs_ca65c1ce:


    rv "Normally, for reasons I've mentioned, we act under the same name.{w} Though I suppose those reasons are all made-up."


translate English day6_rs_937b350b:


    pl "I guess you're actually good at making up stories--unlike your sister."


translate English day6_rs_d0f0646c:


    rv "Heh."


translate English day6_rs_50ad228f:


    pl "What was that problem you mentioned with your appointment?"


translate English day6_rs_6bb7f931:


    rv "Ugh, where should I start..."


translate English day6_rs_8ab8d289:


    rv "My sister is a little bit, really only a tiny bit, different from others.{w} Have you noticed?"


translate English day6_rs_65365980:


    pl "Well, yeah..."


translate English day6_rs_4b6a146d:


    nar "Out of reflex, I look at Rose.{w} She's got that same unreadable expression on her face."


translate English day6_rs_bcb3a8c5:


    pl "I can't really say I didn't notice anything..."


translate English day6_rs_adaef333:


